InterfaceBitmask.name: InterfaceBitmask
InterfaceBitmask.description: An Interface Bitmask used to enable or disable access or functionality of an interface in the system. Each bit in this object represents a network interface in the system consistent with the ifIndex object in MIB-II. The value for this object is interpreted as a bitfield, where the value of 1 means enabled. Examples of Usage: 1. For a system with the following interfaces (AP-2000 & AP-4000): - Ethernet If = 1 - Loopback If = 2 - Wireless If A = 3 - Wireless If B = 4 Interface Bitmask usage: - 00000000 (0x00): All Interfaces disabled - 00000001 (0x01): Ethernet If enabled - 00000010 (0x02): All Interfaces disabled - 00000011 (0x03): Ethernet If enabled - 00000100 (0x04): Wireless If A enabled - 00000110 (0x06): Wireless If A enabled - 00001000 (0x08): Wireless If B enabled - 00001010 (0x0A): Wireless If B enabled - 00001101 (0x0D): All Interfaces enabled - 00001111 (0x0F): All Interfaces enabled (see Note) Note: The software loopback interface bit is ignored in the usage of the interface bitmask object. 2. For a system with the following interfaces (AP-600, AP-700 & Tsunami Multipoint Devices): - Ethernet If = 1 - Loopback If = 2 - Wireless If A = 3 Interface Bitmask usage: - 00000000 (0x00): All Interfaces disabled - 00000001 (0x01): Ethernet If enabled - 00000010 (0x02): All Interfaces disabled - 00000011 (0x03): Ethernet If enabled - 00000100 (0x04): Wireless If A enabled - 00000101 (0x05): All Interfaces enabled - 00000110 (0x06): Wireless If A enabled - 00000111 (0x07): All Interfaces enabled (see Note) Note: The software loopback interface bit is ignored in the usage of the interface bitmask object. 3. For a system with the following interfaces (BG-2000): - Ethernet WAN If = 1 - Ethernet LAN If = 2 - Wireless If A = 3 Inteface Bitmask usage: - 00000000 (0x00): all Interfaces disabled - 00000001 (0x01): Ethernet WAN If enabled - 00000010 (0x02): Ethernet LAN If enabled - 00000011 (0x03): Ethernet WAN and LAN If enabled - 00000100 (0x04): Wireless If A enabled - 00000101 (0x05): Ethernet WAN and Wireless If A enabled - 00000110 (0x06): Ethernet LAN and Wireless If A enabled - 00000111 (0x07): All Interfaces enabled

oriSystemReboot.description: This object is used to reboot the device. The value assigned to this object is the number of seconds until the next reboot.

oriSystemContactEmail.name: oriSystemContactEmail
oriSystemContactEmail.description: This object is used to identify the email address of the contact person for this managed device.

oriSystemContactPhoneNumber.name: oriSystemContactPhoneNumber
oriSystemContactPhoneNumber.description: This object is used to identify the phone number of the contact person for this managed device.

oriSystemFlashUpdate.name: oriSystemFlashUpdate
oriSystemFlashUpdate.description: When this variable is set, all the objects that are to be comitted to flash will be written to flash. This will be done immediately after the value is set, regardless of the value set.

oriSystemFlashBackupInterval.name: oriSystemFlashBackupInterval
oriSystemFlashBackupInterval.description: This object is used for the backup time interval for flash memory to be udpated.

oriSystemEmergencyResetToDefault.name: oriSystemEmergencyResetToDefault
oriSystemEmergencyResetToDefault.description: This object is used to reset the device to factory default values. When this variable is set to 1, all the objects shall be set to factory default values. The default value for this object should be 0.

oriSystemMode.name: oriSystemMode
oriSystemMode.description: This object represents the mode the system is configured to operate in, either bridge or gateway/router mode.

oriSystemEventLogTable.name: oriSystemEventLogTable
oriSystemEventLogTable.description: This table contains system event log information that can include events, errors, and informational messages. This is a circular buffer with a limit 100 entries.

oriSystemEventLogTableEntry.name: oriSystemEventLogTableEntry
oriSystemEventLogTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the system event log table.

oriSystemEventLogMessage.name: oriSystemEventLogMessage
oriSystemEventLogMessage.description: This object is used to store system event log information. This is also used as the index to the table.

oriSystemEventLogTableReset.name: oriSystemEventLogTableReset
oriSystemEventLogTableReset.description: This object is used to reset/clear the event log table. When this object is the set all entries in the event log table are deleted/cleared.

oriSystemEventLogMask.name: oriSystemEventLogMask
oriSystemEventLogMask.description: This object is used to control what events will be logged by the event log facility. It is a mask, each bit is used to enable/disable a corresponding set of log messages. The OR2000 uses the standard syslog priorities and facilities. The Mask should only be set to mask specific facilities. The facilities are: LOG_KERN (0<<3) kernel messages LOG_USER (1<<3) random user-level messages LOG_MAIL (2<<3) mail system LOG_DAEMON (3<<3) system daemons LOG_AUTH (4<<3) authorization messages LOG_SYSLOG (5<<3) messages generated internally by syslogd LOG_LPR (6<<3) line printer subsystem LOG_NEWS (7<<3) network news subsystem LOG_UUCP (8<<3) UUCP subsystem LOG_CRON (9<<3) clock daemon LOG_AUTHPRIV (10<<3) authorization messages (private) LOG_FTP (11<<3) ftp daemon LOG_NTP (12<<3) NTP subsystem LOG_SECURITY (13<<3) security subsystems (firewalling, etc.) LOG_CONSOLE (14<<3) /dev/console output - other codes through 15 reserved for system use LOG_LOCAL0 (16<<3) reserved for local use LOG_LOCAL1 (17<<3) reserved for local use LOG_LOCAL2 (18<<3) reserved for local use LOG_LOCAL3 (19<<3) reserved for local use LOG_LOCAL4 (20<<3) reserved for local use LOG_LOCAL5 (21<<3) reserved for local use LOG_LOCAL6 (22<<3) reserved for local use LOG_LOCAL7 (23<<3) reserved for local use On the BG2000: Each nibble (4 bits == 1 hex digit == a nibble) represents a category of log messages. There are 4 levels of messages per category (1 bit per level per category). The least significant bit is a higher priority message. As follows: security - nibble 1, bits 1-4 errors - nibble 2, bits 5-8 system startup - nibble 3, bits 9-12 warnings - nibble 4, bits 13-16 information - nibble 5, bits 17-20 0x00000 - No events will be logged. 0x000F0 - Only errors will be logged. 0x0F0F0 - Warnings and errors will be logged. 0xFFFFF - All events will be logged.

oriSystemAccessUserName.name: oriSystemAccessUserName
oriSystemAccessUserName.description: This object represents the system access user name for the supported management interfaces (Telnet and HTTP).

oriSystemAccessPassword.name: oriSystemAccessPassword
oriSystemAccessPassword.description: This object represents the system access password for the supported management interfaces (Telnet and HTTP). This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSystemAccessLoginTimeout.name: oriSystemAccessLoginTimeout
oriSystemAccessLoginTimeout.description: This object represents the login timeout in seconds. The default value should be 60 seconds (1 minute).

oriSystemAccessIdleTimeout.name: oriSystemAccessIdleTimeout
oriSystemAccessIdleTimeout.description: This object represents the inactivity or idle timeout in seconds. The default value should be 900 seconds (15 minutes).

oriSystemEventLogNumberOfMessages.name: oriSystemEventLogNumberOfMessages
oriSystemEventLogNumberOfMessages.description: This object represents the number of messages currently stored in the event log table.

oriSystemAccessMaxSessions.name: oriSystemAccessMaxSessions
oriSystemAccessMaxSessions.description: This object controls the maximum number of simultaneous telnet, http, and serial managmenent sessions.

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentIndex.name: oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentIndex
oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentIndex.description: This object represents the table index.

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentSerialNumb.name: oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentSerialNumber

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentName.name: oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentName

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentId.description: This object identifies the system component identification.

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentVariant.name: oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentVariant
oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentVariant.description: This object identifies the system component variant number.

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentReleaseVer.name: oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentReleaseVersion

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentMajorVersi.name: oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentMajorVersion
oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentMajorVersi.description: This object identifies the system component major version number.

oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentMinorVersi.name: oriSystemInvMgmtTableComponentMinorVersion

oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceTableIndex.description: This object identifies the interface table index. This object has been deprecated.

oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceId.name: oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceId
oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceId.description: This object identifies the system component interface identification. This object has been deprecated.

oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceRole.name: oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceRole
oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceRole.description: This object identifies the system component interface role. This object has been deprecated.

oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceVariant.name: oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceVariant
oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceVariant.description: This object identifies the system component's interface variant number. This object has been deprecated.

oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceBottomNumber.name: oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceBottomNumber
oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceBottomNumber.description: This object identifies the system component's interface bottom number. This object has been deprecated.

oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceTopNumber.name: oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceTopNumber
oriSystemInvMgmtInterfaceTopNumber.description: This object identifies the system component's interface top number. This object has been deprecated.

oriSystemFeatureTable.name: oriSystemFeatureTable
oriSystemFeatureTable.description: This table contains a list of features that the current image supports and indicates if this features is licensed (enabled) or not (disabled). Each row represents a supported and/or licensed feature. Supported indicates if the current image supports the image while Licensed indicates that a license is available to use this feature. Based on the license information in this table, some MIB groups/subgroups/tables will be enabled or disabled.

oriSystemFeatureTableEntry.name: oriSystemFeatureTableEntry
oriSystemFeatureTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the system feature license table.

oriSystemFeatureTableCode.name: oriSystemFeatureTableCode
oriSystemFeatureTableCode.description: This object identifies the code for the licensed feature and is used as index for this table.

oriSystemFeatureTableSupported.name: oriSystemFeatureTableSupported
oriSystemFeatureTableSupported.description: This object represents the maximum value for the feature as supported by the current image. For boolean features zero means not supported, non-zero value means supported.

oriSystemFeatureTableLicensed.name: oriSystemFeatureTableLicensed
oriSystemFeatureTableLicensed.description: This object represents the maximum value for the feature as enforced by the license(s). For boolean features zero means not licensed, non-zero value means licensed.

oriSystemFeatureTableDescription.name: oriSystemFeatureTableDescription
oriSystemFeatureTableDescription.description: This object represents a textual description for the licensed feature.

oriSyslogStatus.name: oriSyslogStatus
oriSyslogStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the syslog feature.

oriSyslogPort.name: oriSyslogPort
oriSyslogPort.description: This object represents the UDP destination port number for syslog services. The standard syslog port is 514.

oriSyslogPriority.name: oriSyslogPriority
oriSyslogPriority.description: This object represents the lowest message priority to be logged by the syslog service.

oriSyslogHeartbeatStatus.name: oriSyslogHeartbeatStatus
oriSyslogHeartbeatStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable logging of heartbeat messages by the syslog service.

oriSyslogHeartbeatInterval.name: oriSyslogHeartbeatInterval
oriSyslogHeartbeatInterval.description: This object is used to configure interval (in seconds) for which heartbeat messages will be logged.

oriSyslogHostTable.name: oriSyslogHostTable
oriSyslogHostTable.description: This table is used to configure syslog hosts.

oriSyslogHostTableEntry.name: oriSyslogHostTableEntry
oriSyslogHostTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry for the syslog host table.

oriSyslogHostTableIndex.name: oriSyslogHostTableIndex
oriSyslogHostTableIndex.description: This object represents an index in the syslog host table.

oriSyslogHostIPAddress.name: oriSyslogHostIPAddress
oriSyslogHostIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the host running the syslog daemon.

oriSyslogHostComment.name: oriSyslogHostComment
oriSyslogHostComment.description: This object represents an optional comment for the syslog host, for example the host name or a reference.

oriSyslogHostTableEntryStatus.name: oriSyslogHostTableEntryStatus
oriSyslogHostTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, or create an entry in the syslog host table.

oriUnitTemp.name: oriUnitTemp
oriUnitTemp.description: This object is used for the internal unit temperature in degrees celsius. The range of the temperature is -30 to 60 degrees celsius.

oriTempLoggingInterval.name: oriTempLoggingInterval
oriTempLoggingInterval.description: This object is used for logging interval. The valid values are 1,5,10,15,20,25,30,35,40,45,50,55,and 60.

oriTempLogTable.name: oriTempLogTable
oriTempLogTable.description: This table contains temperature log information. This is a circular buffer with a limit 576 entries.

oriTempLogTableEntry.name: oriTempLogTableEntry
oriTempLogTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the temperature log table.

oriTempLogMessage.name: oriTempLogMessage
oriTempLogMessage.description: This object is used to store temperature log information. This is also used as the index to the table.

oriTempLogTableReset.name: oriTempLogTableReset
oriTempLogTableReset.description: This object is used for resetting the temperature log table.

oriWirelessIfPropertiesTable.name: oriWirelessIfPropertiesTable
oriWirelessIfPropertiesTable.description: This table contains information on the properties and capabilities of the wireless interface(s) present in the device.

oriWirelessIfPropertiesEntry.name: oriWirelessIfPropertiesEntry
oriWirelessIfPropertiesEntry.description: This object represents the entry in the wireless interface properties table.

oriWirelessIfPropertiesIndex.name: oriWirelessIfPropertiesIndex
oriWirelessIfPropertiesIndex.description: This object represents a unique value for each interface in the system and is used as index to this table.

oriWirelessIfNetworkName.name: oriWirelessIfNetworkName
oriWirelessIfNetworkName.description: This object represents the network name (SSID) for this wireless interface.

oriWirelessIfMediumReservation.name: oriWirelessIfMediumReservation
oriWirelessIfMediumReservation.description: This object represents the medium reservation value. The range for this parameter is 0 - 2347. The medium reservation specifies the number of octects in a frame above which a RTS/CTS handshake is performed. The default value should be 2347, which disables RTS/CTS mode.

oriWirelessIfInterferenceRobustness.name: oriWirelessIfInterferenceRobustness
oriWirelessIfInterferenceRobustness.description: This object enables or disables the interference robustness feature. The default value for this object should be disable.

oriWirelessIfDTIMPeriod.name: oriWirelessIfDTIMPeriod
oriWirelessIfDTIMPeriod.description: This object represents the delivery traffic indication map period. This is the interval between the transmission of multicast frames on the wireless inteface. It is expressed in the Beacon messages. The recommended default value for this object is 1.

oriWirelessIfChannel.name: oriWirelessIfChannel
oriWirelessIfChannel.description: This object represents the radio frequency channel for this wireless interface. The default value for the channel is based on the regulatory domain.

oriWirelessIfDistancebetweenAPs.name: oriWirelessIfDistancebetweenAPs
oriWirelessIfDistancebetweenAPs.description: This object identifies the distance between access points. The default value for this parameter should be large.

oriWirelessIfMulticastRate.name: oriWirelessIfMulticastRate
oriWirelessIfMulticastRate.description: This object is used to configure the multicast rate, but it is dependent on the type of wireless NIC. The value of this object is given in 500 Kbps units. This object can be configured to one of the values defined by the supported multicast rates objects (oriWirelessIfSupportedMulticastRates). For 802.11b Wireless NICs: This object identifies multicast rate of the wireless interface. This is dependent on the distance between APs. When the distance between APs object is set to small, minicell, or microcell the multicast rates can be set to 11 Mbit/s (22 in 500 Kbps units), 5.5 Mbit/s (11), 2 Mbit/s (4), and 1 Mbit/s (2). When this object is set to medium, the allowed rates are 5.5 Mbit/s (11), 2 Mbit/s (4), 1 Mbit/s (2). When this object is set to large, then the multicast rates can be set to 2 Mbits/s (4) or 1 Mbits/s (2). The default value for this object should be 2 Mbits/sec (4). For 802.11a, g, and a/g Wireless NICs: This object is used to set the multicast rate for beacons, frames used for protection mechanism (CTS), and other multicast and broadcast frames.

oriWirelessIfClosedSystem.name: oriWirelessIfClosedSystem
oriWirelessIfClosedSystem.description: This object is used as a flag which identifies whether the device will accept association requests to this interface, for client stations configured with a network name of 'ANY'. When this object is disabled, it will accept association requests from client stations with a network name of 'ANY'. If this object is set to enable then the interface will only accept association requests that match the interface's network name (SSID). The default value for this object should be disable.

oriWirelessIfAllowedSupportedDataRates.name: oriWirelessIfAllowedSupportedDataRates
oriWirelessIfAllowedSupportedDataRates.description: This object reflects the transmit rates supported by the wireless interface. The values of this object are given in units of 500 kbps. Examples for supported data rates: - 802.11b PHY (DSSS - 2.4 GHz) - 0 = Auto Fallback - 2 = 1 Mbps - 4 = 2 Mbps - 11 = 5.5 Mbps - 22 = 11 Mbps - 802.11a PHY (OFDM - 5 GHz) - 0 = Auto Fallback - 12 = 6 Mbps - 18 = 9 Mbps - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 108 = 54 Mbps - 802.11a PHY (OFDM - 5 GHz) with Turbo Mode Enabled - 0 = Auto Fallback - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 144 = 72 Mbps - 192 = 96 Mbps - 216 = 108 Mbps - 802.11g PHY (ERP) in 802.11g only mode - 0 = Auto Fallback - 12 = 6 Mbps - 18 = 9 Mbps - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 108 = 54 Mbps - 802.11g PHY (ERP) in 802.11b/g mode - 0 = Auto Fallback - 2 = 1 Mbps - 4 = 2 Mbps - 11 = 5.5 Mbps - 12 = 6 Mbps - 18 = 9 Mbps - 22 = 11 Mbps - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 108 = 54 Mbps

oriWirelessIfRegulatoryDomainList.name: oriWirelessIfRegulatoryDomainList
oriWirelessIfRegulatoryDomainList.description: This object specifies a single regulatory domain (not a list) which is supported by the wireless interface.

oriWirelessIfAllowedChannels.name: oriWirelessIfAllowedChannels
oriWirelessIfAllowedChannels.description: This object reflects the radio frequency channels that the interface supports.

oriWirelessIfMACAddress.name: oriWirelessIfMACAddress
oriWirelessIfMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the wireless interface present in the device. This object has been deprecated.

oriWirelessIfLoadBalancing.name: oriWirelessIfLoadBalancing
oriWirelessIfLoadBalancing.description: This object is used to configure the load balancing feature for the wireless interface.

oriWirelessIfMediumDensityDistribution.name: oriWirelessIfMediumDensityDistribution
oriWirelessIfMediumDensityDistribution.description: This object is used to configure the medium density distribution feature for the wireless interface.

oriWirelessIfTxRate.name: oriWirelessIfTxRate
oriWirelessIfTxRate.description: This object is used to configure the transmit rate for unicast traffic for the wireless interface. This object is dependent on the transmit rates supported by the wireless interface (refer to MIB object - oriWirelessIfAllowedSupportedDataRates and dot11PHYType). The values of this object are given in units of 500 kbps. A value of zero (0) is interpreted as auto fallback. Examples for configuring this object: - 802.11b PHY (DSSS - 2.4 GHz) - 0 = Auto Fallback - 2 = 1 Mbps - 4 = 2 Mbps - 11 = 5.5 Mbps - 22 = 11 Mbps - 802.11a PHY (OFDM - 5 GHz) - 0 = Auto Fallback - 12 = 6 Mbps - 18 = 9 Mbps - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 108 = 54 Mbps - 802.11a PHY (OFDM - 5 GHz) with Turbo Mode Enabled - 0 = Auto Fallback - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 144 = 72 Mbps - 192 = 96 Mbps - 216 = 108 Mbps - 802.11g PHY (ERP) in 802.11g only mode - 0 = Auto Fallback - 12 = 6 Mbps - 18 = 9 Mbps - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 108 = 54 Mbps - 802.11g PHY (ERP) in 802.11b/g mode - 0 = Auto Fallback - 2 = 1 Mbps - 4 = 2 Mbps - 11 = 5.5 Mbps - 12 = 6 Mbps - 18 = 9 Mbps - 22 = 11 Mbps - 24 = 12 Mbps - 36 = 18 Mbps - 48 = 24 Mbps - 72 = 36 Mbps - 96 = 48 Mbps - 108 = 54 Mbps The default value for this object should be zero (0) auto fallback.

oriWirelessIfAutoChannelSelectStatus.name: oriWirelessIfAutoChannelSelectStatus
oriWirelessIfAutoChannelSelectStatus.description: This object is used to configure the automatic frequency channel feature for the wireless interface. If this object is enabled, the frequency channel object can not be set, but the frequency channel selected will be given in that object. The default value for this object should be enable.

oriWirelessIfBandwidthLimitIn.name: oriWirelessIfBandwidthLimitIn
oriWirelessIfBandwidthLimitIn.description: This object represents the input bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriWirelessIfBandwidthLimitOut.name: oriWirelessIfBandwidthLimitOut
oriWirelessIfBandwidthLimitOut.description: This object represents the output bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriWirelessIfTurboModeStatus.name: oriWirelessIfTurboModeStatus
oriWirelessIfTurboModeStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable turbo mode support. Turbo mode is only supported for 802.11a PHY (OFDM - 5 GHz) and 802.11g (ERP - 2.4 GHz) wireless NICs and can only be enabled when super mode is enabled. When Turbo mode is enabled the data rates will be doubled (refer to oriWirelessIfAllowedSupportedDataRates object description).

oriWirelessIfSupportedOperationalModes.name: oriWirelessIfSupportedOperationalModes
oriWirelessIfSupportedOperationalModes.description: This object provides information on the wireless operational modes supported by the NIC. Depending on the wireless NIC in the device different wireless operational modes can be configured. The possible supported modes can be: - 802.11b only - 802.11g only - 802.11b/g - 802.11a only - 802.11g-wifi

oriWirelessIfOperationalMode.name: oriWirelessIfOperationalMode
oriWirelessIfOperationalMode.description: This object is used to set the wireless NIC Operational mode. Depending on the wireless NIC in the device different wireless operational modes can be configured. The supported modes are: - 802.11b only - 802.11g only - 802.11b/g - 802.11a only - 802.11g-wifi

oriWirelessIfPreambleType.name: oriWirelessIfPreambleType
oriWirelessIfPreambleType.description: This object identifies the wireless interface preamble type based on the wireless operational mode configured.

oriWirelessIfProtectionMechanismStatus.name: oriWirelessIfProtectionMechanismStatus
oriWirelessIfProtectionMechanismStatus.description: This object indicates if protection mechanism is enabled or not based on the wireless operational mode configured.

oriWirelessIfSupportedMulticastRates.name: oriWirelessIfSupportedMulticastRates
oriWirelessIfSupportedMulticastRates.description: This object represents the multicast rates supported by the wireless NIC and the operational mode configured.

oriWirelessIfCapabilities.name: oriWirelessIfCapabilities
oriWirelessIfCapabilities.description: This object provides information on the wireless capabilities and features supported by the wireless NIC. Each bit in this object defines a capability/feature supported by the wireless NIC. If the bit is set, the capability/feature is supported, otherwise it is not. The following list provides a definition of the bits in this object: b0 - Distance Between APs b1 - Multicast Rate b2 - Closed System b3 - Load Balancing b4 - Medium Density Distribution b5 - Auto Channel Select b6 - Turbo Mode b7 - Interference Robustness b8 - Wireless Distribution System (WDS) b9 - Transmit Power Control (TPC) b10 - Multiple SSIDs b11 - SpectraLink VoIP b12 - Remote Link Test b13 to b255 - Reserved

oriWirelessIfLBTxTimeThreshold.name: oriWirelessIfLBTxTimeThreshold
oriWirelessIfLBTxTimeThreshold.description: Maximum allowed Tx processing time, in mS, where Tx processing time is measured from time a packet enters AP from the DS to the time it successfully leaves the AP's Radio.

oriWirelessIfLBAdjAPTimeDiffThreshold.name: oriWirelessIfLBAdjAPTimeDiffThreshold
oriWirelessIfLBAdjAPTimeDiffThreshold.description: Maximum allowed difference in mS between adjacent AP's Tx processing time.

oriWirelessIfACSFrequencyBandScan.name: oriWirelessIfACSFrequencyBandScan
oriWirelessIfACSFrequencyBandScan.description: This object is used to configure the frequency bands that the auto channel select algorithm will scan through. Each bit in this object represents a band or subset of channels in the 5 GHz or 2.4 GHz space. The value of this object is interpreted as a bitfield, where the value of 1 means enable ACS scan for that band. The following list provides a definition of the bits in this object: b0 - U-NII Lower Band = 5.15 - 5.25 GHz (36, 40, 44, 48) b1 - U-NII Middle Band = 5.25 - 5.35 GHz (52, 56, 60, 64) b2 - U-NII Upper Band = 5.725 - 5.825 GHz (149, 153, 157, 161) b3 - H Band = 5.50 - 5.700 GHz (100, 104, 108, 112, 116, 120, 124, 128, 132, 136, 140) b4 - 5 GHz ISM Band = 5.825 GHz (165) b5 to b255 - Reserved

oriWirelessIfSecurityPerSSIDStatus.name: oriWirelessIfSecurityPerSSIDStatus
oriWirelessIfSecurityPerSSIDStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the security per SSID feature. Once this object is enabled, the administrator should use the Wireless Interface SSID table (oriWirelessIfSSIDTable to configure the security related management objects.

oriWirelessIfDFSStatus.name: oriWirelessIfDFSStatus
oriWirelessIfDFSStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable dynamic frequency selection. This functionality is dependent on the regulatory domain of the wireless NIC.

oriWirelessIfAntenna.name: oriWirelessIfAntenna
oriWirelessIfAntenna.description: This object is used to configure the antenna. The administrator can select controllable, external, internal, or disable the antenna.

oriWirelessIfTPCMode.name: oriWirelessIfTPCMode
oriWirelessIfTPCMode.description: This object is used to configure the transmit power control of the wireless NIC. The transmit power is defined in dBm and can be configured in increments 3 dBms.

oriWirelessIfSuperModeStatus.name: oriWirelessIfSuperModeStatus
oriWirelessIfSuperModeStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable super mode support. Super Mode increases the overall throughput of the wireless interface by implementing fast frame, bursting, and compression. When super mode is enabled, the channels that can be used in the 2.4 GHz and 5.0 GHz spectrum are limited (refer to oriWirelessIfAllowedChannels for the allowed channels). The super mode feature is only supported for 802.11a (OFDM - 5 GHz) and 802.11g (ERP - 2.4 GHz) wireless NICs.

oriWirelessIfWSSStatus.name: oriWirelessIfWSSStatus
oriWirelessIfWSSStatus.description: This object is used for the Wireless System Shutdown feature. This feature allows an administrator to shut down wireless services to clients. When this object is set to down wireless client services will be shutdown/disabled, but WDS links will still remain up.

oriWirelessIfSupportedAuthenticationMode.name: oriWirelessIfSupportedAuthenticationModes
oriWirelessIfSupportedAuthenticationMode.description: This object is used to provide information on the authentication modes supported by the wireless interface. The possible authentication modes are: - none: no authentication mode - dot1x: 802.1x authentication mode - psk: psk authentication mode

oriWirelessIfSupportedCipherModes.name: oriWirelessIfSupportedCipherModes
oriWirelessIfSupportedCipherModes.description: This object is used to provide information on the cipher modes/types supported by the wireless interface. The possible cipher modes/types are: - none: no cipher/encryption mode - wep: wep encryption mode - tkip: tkip encryption mode - aes: aes encryption mode

oriWirelessIfQoSStatus.name: oriWirelessIfQoSStatus
oriWirelessIfQoSStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable Quality of Service (QoS) on the wireless interface.

oriWirelessIfQoSMaxMediumThreshold.name: oriWirelessIfQoSMaxMediumThreshold
oriWirelessIfQoSMaxMediumThreshold.description: This object is used to specify the QoS admission control maximum medium threshold. The maximum medium threshold will apply to all access categories and is given in a percentage of the medium.

oriWirelessIfAntennaGain.name: oriWirelessIfAntennaGain
oriWirelessIfAntennaGain.description: This object represents Antenna Gain value (including cable loss) that will be added to the radar detetection parameters.

oriWirelessIfSecurityTable.name: oriWirelessIfSecurityTable
oriWirelessIfSecurityTable.description: This table contains information on the security management objects for the wireless interface(s) present in the device.

oriWirelessIfSecurityEntry.name: oriWirelessIfSecurityEntry
oriWirelessIfSecurityEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the wireless interface security table.

oriWirelessIfSecurityIndex.name: oriWirelessIfSecurityIndex
oriWirelessIfSecurityIndex.description: This object represents a unique value for each interface in the system and is used as index to this table.

oriWirelessIfEncryptionOptions.name: oriWirelessIfEncryptionOptions
oriWirelessIfEncryptionOptions.description: This object sets the wireless interface's security capabilities (such as WEP and other standard and proprietary security features). AES encryption is only for 802.11a and supports only OCB mode integrity check.

oriWirelessIfEncryptionStatus.name: oriWirelessIfEncryptionStatus
oriWirelessIfEncryptionStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable WEP encryption for the wireless interface.

oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey1.name: oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey1
oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey1.description: This object represents Encryption Key 1. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey2.name: oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey2
oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey2.description: This object represents Encryption Key 2. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey3.name: oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey3
oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey3.description: This object represents Encryption Key 3. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey4.name: oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey4
oriWirelessIfEncryptionKey4.description: This object represents Encryption Key 4. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriWirelessIfEncryptionTxKey.name: oriWirelessIfEncryptionTxKey
oriWirelessIfEncryptionTxKey.description: This object indicates which encryption key is used to encrypt data that is sent via the wireless interfaces. When this object is configured to 0, then Encryption Key 1 will be used. When this object is configured to 1, then Encryption Key 2 will be used. When this object is configured to 2, then Encryption Key 3 will be used. When this object is configured to 3, then Encryption Key 4 will be used. The default value for this object should be key 0.

oriWirelessIfDenyNonEncryptedData.name: oriWirelessIfDenyNonEncryptedData
oriWirelessIfDenyNonEncryptedData.description: This parameter indicates if this interface will accept or deny non-encrypted data. The default value for this parameters is disabled.

oriWirelessIfProfileCode.name: oriWirelessIfProfileCode
oriWirelessIfProfileCode.description: The object represents the profile code of the wirelesss interface. This information is comprised of a vendor indication and a capability indication (example: bronze or gold card).

oriWirelessIfSSIDTable.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTable
oriWirelessIfSSIDTable.description: This table is used to configure the SSIDs for the wireless interface in the device.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEntry.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEntry
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the respective table. In this case each table entry represents a VLAN ID.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableIndex.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableIndex
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableIndex.description: This object represents the index to the SSID Table.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSSID.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSSID
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSSID.description: This object represents the wireless card SSID string (wireless network name).

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableVLANID.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableVLANID
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableVLANID.description: This object represents the VLAN Identifier (ID).

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableStatus.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableStatus
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableStatus.description: This object represents the wireless SSID table row/entry status.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSecurityMode.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSecurityMode
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSecurityMode.description: This object is used to configure the security mode for this table entry (SSID). This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableBroadcastSSID.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableBroadcastSSID
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableBroadcastSSID.description: This object is used to enable/disable a broadcast SSID in the SSID table. A single entry in the SSID table can be enabled to broadcast SSID in beacon messages.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableClosedSystem.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableClosedSystem
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableClosedSystem.description: This object is used to enable/disable the closed system feature for this table entry (SSID).

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSupportedSecurityM.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSupportedSecurityModes
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSupportedSecurityM.description: This object is used to provide information on the supported security modes by the wireless interface(s). The possible security modes can be: - None: no security mode enabled. - dot1x: 802.1x authentication enabled. - mixed: mixed WEP and 802.1x. - wpa: WiFi Protected Access enabled. - wpa-psk: WiFi Protected Access with Preshared Keys enabled. - wep: WEP Encryption enabled (no authentication) This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey0.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey0
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey0.description: This object represents Encryption Key 0. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey1.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey1
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey1.description: This object represents Encryption Key 1. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey2.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey2
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey2.description: This object represents Encryption Key 2. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey3.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey3
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKey3.description: This object represents Encryption Key 3. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionTxKey.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionTxKey
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionTxKey.description: This object indicates which encryption key is used to encrypt data that is sent via the wireless interfaces. The default value for this object should be key 0. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKeyLengt.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKeyLength
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableEncryptionKeyLengt.description: This object represents the encryption key length, the supported key lengths are 64 bits (40 + 24 for IV), 128 bits (104 + 24 for IV), and 152 bits (128 + 24 for IV). This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRekeyingInterval.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRekeyingInterval
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRekeyingInterval.description: This object represents the encryption rekeying interval. if this object is configured to zero (0) rekeying is disabled. The units of this object is seconds.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKValue.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKValue
oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKValue.description: The Pre-Shared Key (PSK) for when RSN in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite. In that case, the PMK will obtain its value from this object. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKPassPhrase.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKPassPhrase
oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKPassPhrase.description: The PSK, for when RSN in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite, is configured by oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKValue. An alternative manner of setting the PSK uses the password-to-key algorithm defined in the standard. This variable provides a means to enter a pass phrase. When this object is written, the RSN entity shall use the password-to-key algorithm specified in the standard to derive a pre-shared and populate oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKValue with this key. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableDenyNonEncryptedDa.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableDenyNonEncryptedData
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableDenyNonEncryptedDa.description: This object is used to enable/disable deny non encrypted data. This function is only supported when the security mode is configured to WEP or Mixed Mode; it is not supported for 802.1x, WPA, and WPA-PSK security modes. This object is deprecated.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSSIDAuthorizationS.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSSIDAuthorizationStatus
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSSIDAuthorizationS.description: This object is used to enable or disable SSID Authorization.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableMACAccessControl.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableMACAccessControl
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableMACAccessControl.description: This object is used to enable or disable MAC Access Control feature/filter for this SSID.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSMACAccessCon.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSMACAccessControl
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSMACAccessCon.description: This object is used to enables RADIUS Access Control based on wireless stations MAC Address.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSecurityProfile.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSecurityProfile
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableSecurityProfile.description: This object is used to configure the security profile that will be used for this SSID. The security profile is defined in the Security Profile Table in the orinocoSecurity group.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSDot1xProfile.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSDot1xProfile
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSDot1xProfile.description: This object is used to configure the RADIUS server profile that will be used for 802.1x authentication for this SSID. The RADIUS profile is defined in the RADIUS Server Table in the orinocoRADIUSSvrProfile group.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSMACAuthProfi.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSMACAuthProfile
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSMACAuthProfi.description: This object is used to configure the RADIUS server profile that will be used for MAC based RADIUS authentication for this SSID. The RADIUS profile is defined in the RADIUS Server Table in the orinocoRADIUSSvrProfile group.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSAccountingSt.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSAccountingStatus
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSAccountingSt.description: This object is used to enable or disable the RADIUS Accounting service per SSID.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSAccountingPr.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSAccountingProfile
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableRADIUSAccountingPr.description: This object is used to configure the RADIUS server profile that will be used for Accounting for this SSID. The RADIUS profile is defined in the RADIUS Server Table in the orinocoRADIUSSvrProfile group.

oriWirelessIfSSIDTableQoSPolicy.name: oriWirelessIfSSIDTableQoSPolicy
oriWirelessIfSSIDTableQoSPolicy.description: This object is used to configure the QoS policy that will be used for this SSID. The QoS profile is defined in the QoS Policy Table in the orinocoQoS group.

oriWirelessIfTxPowerControl.name: oriWirelessIfTxPowerControl
oriWirelessIfTxPowerControl.description: This object is used to enable or disable Transmit (Tx) Power Control feature.

oriEthernetIfConfigTable.name: oriEthernetIfConfigTable
oriEthernetIfConfigTable.description: This table is used to configure the ethernet interface(s) for the device.

oriEthernetIfConfigTableEntry.name: oriEthernetIfConfigTableEntry
oriEthernetIfConfigTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the ethernet interface configuration table.

oriEthernetIfConfigTableIndex.name: oriEthernetIfConfigTableIndex
oriEthernetIfConfigTableIndex.description: This object represents the index of the ethernet configuraiton table.

oriEthernetIfConfigSettings.name: oriEthernetIfConfigSettings
oriEthernetIfConfigSettings.description: This object is used to configure the Ethernet interface's speed. Some devices support all the configuration options listed above, while others support only a subset of the configuration options.

oriEthernetIfConfigBandwidthLimitIn.name: oriEthernetIfConfigBandwidthLimitIn
oriEthernetIfConfigBandwidthLimitIn.description: This object represents the input bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration, or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriEthernetIfConfigBandwidthLimitOut.name: oriEthernetIfConfigBandwidthLimitOut
oriEthernetIfConfigBandwidthLimitOut.description: This object represents the output bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration, or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriIfWANInterfaceMACAddress.name: oriIfWANInterfaceMACAddress
oriIfWANInterfaceMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the WAN interface.

oriWORPIfConfigTable.name: oriWORPIfConfigTable
oriWORPIfConfigTable.description: This table is used to configure the mode, time-outs, and protocol objects for wireless interface(s) that are configured to run WORP.

oriWORPIfConfigTableEntry.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableEntry
oriWORPIfConfigTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the WORP Interface Configuration Table.

oriWORPIfConfigTableMode.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableMode
oriWORPIfConfigTableMode.description: The running mode of this interface: - If set to disabled, the interface is disabled. - If set to AP, the interface will run in standard IEEE802.11 mode. - If set to Base, the interface will be a WORP master interface and be able to connect to multiple WORP satellites. - If set to Satellite, the interface will be a WORP slave interface.

oriWORPIfConfigTableBaseStationName.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableBaseStationName
oriWORPIfConfigTableBaseStationName.description: The name of the base station. For a base this name will default to the MIB-II sysName; for a satellite to empty (if not registered to any base) or the name it is registered to. When a name is set for a satellite, the satellite will only register on a base with this name.

oriWORPIfConfigTableMaxSatellites.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableMaxSatellites
oriWORPIfConfigTableMaxSatellites.description: The maximum of remotes allowed on this interface. Please note that this value will also be limited by the image and the license.

oriWORPIfConfigTableRegistrationTimeout.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableRegistrationTimeout
oriWORPIfConfigTableRegistrationTimeout.description: This object represents the Timeout of regristration and authentication, configurable between 1sec and 10sec.

oriWORPIfConfigTableRetries.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableRetries
oriWORPIfConfigTableRetries.description: The number of times a data message will be retransmitted, configurable between 0 and 10. The value 0 allows unreliable operation for streaming applications.

oriWORPIfConfigTableNetworkSecret.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableNetworkSecret
oriWORPIfConfigTableNetworkSecret.description: The NetworkSecret is a string that must be the same for all stations in a certain network. If a station has another secret configured as the base, the base will not allow the station to register. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriWORPIfConfigTableNoSleepMode.name: oriWORPIfConfigTableNoSleepMode
oriWORPIfConfigTableNoSleepMode.description: This object is used to enable or disable sleep mode. If this object is enabled, a subscriber unit will not go into sleep mode when they have no data to send.

oriWORPIfStatTable.name: oriWORPIfStatTable
oriWORPIfStatTable.description: This table is used to monitor the statistics of interfaces that run WORP.

oriWORPIfStatTableEntry.name: oriWORPIfStatTableEntry
oriWORPIfStatTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the WORP Interface Statistics Table.

oriWORPIfStatTableRemotePartners.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRemotePartners
oriWORPIfStatTableRemotePartners.description: The number of remote partners. For a satellite, this parameter will always be zero or one.

oriWORPIfStatTableAverageLocalSignal.name: oriWORPIfStatTableAverageLocalSignal
oriWORPIfStatTableAverageLocalSignal.description: The current signal level calculated over all inbound packets. This variable indicates the running average of the local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfStatTableAverageLocalNoise.name: oriWORPIfStatTableAverageLocalNoise
oriWORPIfStatTableAverageLocalNoise.description: The current noise level calculated over all inbound packets. This variable indicates the running average of the local noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfStatTableAverageRemoteSignal.name: oriWORPIfStatTableAverageRemoteSignal
oriWORPIfStatTableAverageRemoteSignal.description: The current remote signal level calculated over the inbound packets send by this station. This variable indicates the running average over all registered stations of the remote signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfStatTableAverageRemoteNoise.name: oriWORPIfStatTableAverageRemoteNoise
oriWORPIfStatTableAverageRemoteNoise.description: The current average remote noise level calculated over the inbound packets send by this station. This variable indicates the running average over all registered stations of the remote noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfStatTableBaseStationAnnounces.name: oriWORPIfStatTableBaseStationAnnounces
oriWORPIfStatTableBaseStationAnnounces.description: The number of Base Station Announces Broadcasts (BSAB) sent (base) or received (satellite) on this interface.

oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationRequests.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationRequests
oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationRequests.description: The number of Registration Requests (RREQ) sent (satellite) or received (base) on this interface.

oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationRejects.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationRejects
oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationRejects.description: The number of Registration Rejects (RREJ) sent (base) or received (satellite) on this interface.

oriWORPIfStatTableAuthenticationRequests.name: oriWORPIfStatTableAuthenticationRequests
oriWORPIfStatTableAuthenticationRequests.description: The number of Authentication Requests (AREQ) sent (satellite) or received (base) on this interface.

oriWORPIfStatTableAuthenticationConfirms.name: oriWORPIfStatTableAuthenticationConfirms
oriWORPIfStatTableAuthenticationConfirms.description: The number of Authentication Confirms (ACFM) sent (base) or received (satellite) on this interface.

oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationAttempts.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationAttempts
oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationAttempts.description: The number of times a Registration Attempt has been initiated.

oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationIncomplete.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationIncompletes
oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationIncomplete.description: The number of registration attempts that is not completed yet. For a satellite this parameters will always be zero or one.

oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationTimeouts.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationTimeouts
oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationTimeouts.description: The number of times the registration procedure timed out.

oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationLastReason.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationLastReason
oriWORPIfStatTableRegistrationLastReason.description: The reason for why the last registration was aborted or failed.

oriWORPIfStatTablePollData.name: oriWORPIfStatTablePollData
oriWORPIfStatTablePollData.description: The number of polls with data sent (base) or received (satellite).

oriWORPIfStatTablePollNoData.name: oriWORPIfStatTablePollNoData
oriWORPIfStatTablePollNoData.description: The number of polls with no data sent (base) or received (satellite).

oriWORPIfStatTableReplyData.name: oriWORPIfStatTableReplyData
oriWORPIfStatTableReplyData.description: The number of poll replies with data sent (satellite) or received (base). This counter does not include replies with the MoreData flag set (see ReplyMoreData).

oriWORPIfStatTableReplyMoreData.name: oriWORPIfStatTableReplyMoreData
oriWORPIfStatTableReplyMoreData.description: The number of poll replies with data sent (satellite) or received (base) with the MoreData flag set (see also ReplyData).

oriWORPIfStatTableReplyNoData.name: oriWORPIfStatTableReplyNoData
oriWORPIfStatTableReplyNoData.description: The number of poll replies with no data sent (satellite) or received (base).

oriWORPIfStatTableRequestForService.name: oriWORPIfStatTableRequestForService
oriWORPIfStatTableRequestForService.description: The number of requests for service sent (satellite) or received (base).

oriWORPIfStatTableSendSuccess.name: oriWORPIfStatTableSendSuccess
oriWORPIfStatTableSendSuccess.description: The number of data packets sent that were acknowledged and did not need a retransmit.

oriWORPIfStatTableSendRetries.name: oriWORPIfStatTableSendRetries
oriWORPIfStatTableSendRetries.description: The number of data packets sent that needed retransmition but were finally received succesfully by the remote partner.

oriWORPIfStatTableSendFailures.name: oriWORPIfStatTableSendFailures
oriWORPIfStatTableSendFailures.description: The number of data packets sent that were (finally) not received succesfully by the remote partner.

oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveSuccess.name: oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveSuccess
oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveSuccess.description: The number of data packets received that were acknowledged and did not need a retransmit of the remote partner.

oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveRetries.name: oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveRetries
oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveRetries.description: The number of data packets received that needed retransmition by the remote partner but were finally received succesfully.

oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveFailures.name: oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveFailures
oriWORPIfStatTableReceiveFailures.description: The number of data packets that were (finally) not received succesfully.

oriWORPIfStatTablePollNoReplies.name: oriWORPIfStatTablePollNoReplies
oriWORPIfStatTablePollNoReplies.description: The number of times a poll was sent but no reply was received. This object only applies to the base.

oriWORPIfSatConfigStatus.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigStatus
oriWORPIfSatConfigStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the per-satellite config from the base device.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTable.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTable
oriWORPIfSatConfigTable.description: This table contains wireless stations statistics.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableEntry.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableEntry
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the WORP Interface Satellite Statistics Table.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableIndex.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableIndex
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableIndex.description: This object is used to index the protocol filter table.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableEntryStatus.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableEntryStatus
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create the Ethernet protocols in this table.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMacAddress.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMacAddress
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMacAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the satellite for which the statistics are gathered.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMinimumBandwidthL.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMinimumBandwidthLimitDownlink
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMinimumBandwidthL.description: This object represents the minimum input bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMaximumBandwidthL.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMaximumBandwidthLimitDownlink
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMaximumBandwidthL.description: This object represents the maximum input bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMinimumBandwidthL.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMinimumBandwidthLimitUplink
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMinimumBandwidthL.description: This object represents the minimum output bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMaximumBandwidthL.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMaximumBandwidthLimitUplink
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableMaximumBandwidthL.description: This object represents the maximum output bandwidth limit of the interface in increments of 64 kbps. The value can be limited by a previous written value, the negotiation process during registration or by a license. A written value will only take effect after reboot.

oriWORPIfSatConfigTableComment.name: oriWORPIfSatConfigTableComment
oriWORPIfSatConfigTableComment.description: This object is used for an optional comment associated to the per Satellite config Table entry.

oriWORPIfSatStatTable.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTable
oriWORPIfSatStatTable.description: This table contains wireless stations statistics.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableEntry.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableEntry
oriWORPIfSatStatTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the WORP Interface Satellite Statistics Table.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableIndex.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableIndex
oriWORPIfSatStatTableIndex.description: This object represents the table index for SatStat Table.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableMacAddress.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableMacAddress
oriWORPIfSatStatTableMacAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the satellite for which the statistics are gathered.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageLocalSignal.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageLocalSignal
oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageLocalSignal.description: The current signal level calculated over all inbound packets. This variable indicates the running average of the local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageLocalNoise.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageLocalNoise
oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageLocalNoise.description: The current noise level calculated over all inbound packets. This variable indicates the running average of the local noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageRemoteSignal.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageRemoteSignal
oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageRemoteSignal.description: The current remote signal level calculated over the inbound packets send by this station. This variable indicates the running average over all registered stations of the remote signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageRemoteNoise.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageRemoteNoise
oriWORPIfSatStatTableAverageRemoteNoise.description: The current average remote noise level calculated over the inbound packets send by this station. This variable indicates the running average over all registered stations of the remote noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollData.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollData
oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollData.description: The number of polls with data sent (base) or received (satellite).

oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollNoData.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollNoData
oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollNoData.description: The number of polls with no data sent (base) or received (satellite).

oriWORPIfSatStatTableReplyData.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableReplyData
oriWORPIfSatStatTableReplyData.description: The number of poll replies with data sent (satellite) or received (base). This counter does not include replies with the MoreData flag set (see ReplyMoreData).

oriWORPIfSatStatTableReplyNoData.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableReplyNoData
oriWORPIfSatStatTableReplyNoData.description: The number of poll replies with no data sent (satellite) or received (base).

oriWORPIfSatStatTableRequestForService.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableRequestForService
oriWORPIfSatStatTableRequestForService.description: The number of requests for service sent (satellite) or received (base).

oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendSuccess.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendSuccess
oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendSuccess.description: The number of data packets sent that were acknowledged and did not need a retransmit.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendRetries.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendRetries
oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendRetries.description: The number of data packets sent that needed retransmition but were finally received succesfully by the remote partner.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendFailures.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendFailures
oriWORPIfSatStatTableSendFailures.description: The number of data packets sent that were (finally) not received succesfully by the remote partner.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveSuccess.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveSuccess
oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveSuccess.description: The number of data packets received that were acknowledged and did not need a retransmit of the remote partner.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveRetries.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveRetries
oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveRetries.description: The number of data packets received that needed retransmition by the remote partner but were finally received succesfully.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveFailures.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveFailures
oriWORPIfSatStatTableReceiveFailures.description: The number of data packets that were (finally) not received succesfully.

oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollNoReplies.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollNoReplies
oriWORPIfSatStatTablePollNoReplies.description: The number of times a poll was sent but no reply was received. This object only applies to the base.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableLocalTxRate.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableLocalTxRate
oriWORPIfSatStatTableLocalTxRate.description: This object represents the Transmit Data Rate of the BSU.

oriWORPIfSatStatTableRemoteTxRate.name: oriWORPIfSatStatTableRemoteTxRate
oriWORPIfSatStatTableRemoteTxRate.description: This object represents the Transmit Data Rate of the SU which is registered to this SU.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyOperation.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyOperation
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyOperation.description: This object is used to enable or disable the site survey mode. The site survey is going to show user the wireless signal level, noise level and SNR value.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyTable.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyTable
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyTable.description: This table contains the information for the stations currently associated with the access point.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveySignalQualityTableEnt.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveySignalQualityTableEntry
oriWORPIfSiteSurveySignalQualityTableEnt.description: This object represents the entry in the Remote Link Test table.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyTableIndex.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyTableIndex
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyTableIndex.description: This object represents a unique entry in the table.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyBaseMACAddress.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyBaseMACAddress
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyBaseMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the base unit being tested with.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyBaseName.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyBaseName
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyBaseName.description: This object identifies the name of the base unit being tested with..

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyMaxSatAllowed.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyMaxSatAllowed
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyMaxSatAllowed.description: This object identifies the maximum number of satellites is allowed to be registered with the base unit being tested with.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyNumSatRegistered.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyNumSatRegistered
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyNumSatRegistered.description: This object identifies the maximum number of satellites is allowed to be registered with the base unit being tested with.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyCurrentSatRegistered.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyCurrentSatRegistered
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyCurrentSatRegistered.description: This object identifies the maximum number of satellites is allowed to be registered with the base unit being tested with.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalSignalLevel.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalSignalLevel
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalSignalLevel.description: The current signal level (in dB) for the Site Survey from this station. This object indicates the running average of the local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalNoiseLevel.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalNoiseLevel
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalNoiseLevel.description: The current noise level (in dB) for the Site Survey to this station. This object indicates the running average of the local noise level.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalSNR.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalSNR
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyLocalSNR.description: The current signal to noise ratio for the Site Survey to this station.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteSignalLevel.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteSignalLevel
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteSignalLevel.description: The current signal level (in dB) for the Site Survey from the base with which the current satellite is registered. This object indicates the running average of the local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteNoiseLevel.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteNoiseLevel
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteNoiseLevel.description: The current noise level (in dB) for the Site Survey from the base with which the current satellite is registered.

oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteSNR.name: oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteSNR
oriWORPIfSiteSurveyRemoteSNR.description: The current SNR (in dB) for the Site Survey from the base with which the current satellite is registered.

oriWORPIfDDRSStatus.name: oriWORPIfDDRSStatus
oriWORPIfDDRSStatus.description: This is object is used to enable/disable the WORP DDRS feature on the BSU.

oriWORPIfDDRSDefDataRate.name: oriWORPIfDDRSDefDataRate
oriWORPIfDDRSDefDataRate.description: This is the data rate that shall be used only when DDRS is enabled. This is to specify default data rate on BSU. The possible values of the variable shall be: 1. 802.11a normal mode 6Mbps 2. 802.11a normal mode 9Mbps 3. 802.11a normal mode 12Mbps 4. 802.11a normal mode 18Mbps 5. 802.11a normal mode 24Mbps 6. 802.11a normal mode 36Mbps 7. 802.11a normal mode 48Mbps 8. 802.11a normal mode 54Mbps 9. 802.11a turbo mode 12Mbps 10. 802.11a turbo mode 18Mbps 11. 802.11a turbo mode 24Mbps 12. 802.11a turbo mode 36Mbps 13. 802.11a turbo mode 48Mbps 14. 802.11a turbo mode 72Mbps 15. 802.11a turbo mode 96Mbps 16. 802.11a turbo mode 108Mbps

oriWORPIfDDRSMaxDataRate.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMaxDataRate
oriWORPIfDDRSMaxDataRate.description: This is the data rate that shall be used only when DDRS is enabled. This is to limit maximum possible data rate that is set by DDRS on BSU. The possible values of the variable shall be: 1. 802.11a normal mode 6Mbps 2. 802.11a normal mode 9Mbps 3. 802.11a normal mode 12Mbps 4. 802.11a normal mode 18Mbps 5. 802.11a normal mode 24Mbps 6. 802.11a normal mode 36Mbps 7. 802.11a normal mode 48Mbps 8. 802.11a normal mode 54Mbps 9. 802.11a turbo mode 12Mbps 10. 802.11a turbo mode 18Mbps 11. 802.11a turbo mode 24Mbps 12. 802.11a turbo mode 36Mbps 13. 802.11a turbo mode 48Mbps 14. 802.11a turbo mode 72Mbps 15. 802.11a turbo mode 96Mbps 16. 802.11a turbo mode 108Mbps

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an6Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an6Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an6Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 6Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 6dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an9Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an9Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an9Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 9Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 7dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an12Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an12Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an12Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 12Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 9dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an18Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an18Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an18Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 18Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 11dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an24Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an24Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an24Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 24Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 14dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an36Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an36Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an36Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 36Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 18dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an48Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an48Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an48Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 48Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 22dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an54Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an54Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11an54Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 54Mbps on 802.11a radio, normal mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 25dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at12Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at12Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at12Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 12Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 6dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at18Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at18Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at18Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 18Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 7dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at24Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at24Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at24Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 24Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 9dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at36Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at36Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at36Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 36Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 11dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at48Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at48Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at48Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 48Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 14dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at72Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at72Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at72Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 72Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 18dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at96Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at96Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at96Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 96Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 22dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at108Mbps.name: oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at108Mbps
oriWORPIfDDRSMinReqSNRdot11at108Mbps.description: This is to specify the minimum required SNR for data rate of 108Mbps on 802.11a radio, turbo mode. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 25dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncAvgSNRThreshold.name: oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncAvgSNRThreshold
oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncAvgSNRThreshold.description: This is to specify average SNR threshold for data rate increase. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 4 dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncReqSNRThreshold.name: oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncReqSNRThreshold
oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncReqSNRThreshold.description: This is to specify average SNR threshold for data rate decrease. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 6 dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateDecReqSNRThreshold.name: oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateDecReqSNRThreshold
oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateDecReqSNRThreshold.description: This is to specify SNRreq threshold for data rate reduction. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB. The default value should be 3 dB.

oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncPercentThreshold.name: oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncPercentThreshold
oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateIncPercentThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold percentage of retransmissions for DDRS data rate increase.

oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateDecPercentThreshold.name: oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateDecPercentThreshold
oriWORPIfDDRSDataRateDecPercentThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold percentage of retransmissions for DDRS data rate decrease.

oriWORPIfRoamingStatus.name: oriWORPIfRoamingStatus
oriWORPIfRoamingStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable Roaming between BSUs.

oriWORPIfRoamingSlowScanThreshold.name: oriWORPIfRoamingSlowScanThreshold
oriWORPIfRoamingSlowScanThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold for initiating slow scanning procedure. The units of this object is dBs.

oriWORPIfRoamingFastScanThreshold.name: oriWORPIfRoamingFastScanThreshold
oriWORPIfRoamingFastScanThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold for initiating fast scanning procedure. The units of this object is dBs.

oriWORPIfRoamingThreshold.name: oriWORPIfRoamingThreshold
oriWORPIfRoamingThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold for roaming threshold. The units of this object is dBs.

oriWORPIfRoamingSlowScanPercentThreshold.name: oriWORPIfRoamingSlowScanPercentThreshold
oriWORPIfRoamingSlowScanPercentThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold percentage of retransmissions for initiating slow scanning procedure.

oriWORPIfRoamingFastScanPercentThreshold.name: oriWORPIfRoamingFastScanPercentThreshold
oriWORPIfRoamingFastScanPercentThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold percentage of retransmissions for initiating fast scanning procedure.

orinocoWORPIfBSUStatMACAddress.name: orinocoWORPIfBSUStatMACAddress
orinocoWORPIfBSUStatMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of BSU to which the SU is registered.

orinocoWORPIfBSUStatLocalTxRate.name: orinocoWORPIfBSUStatLocalTxRate
orinocoWORPIfBSUStatLocalTxRate.description: This object represents the Transmit Data Rate of the SU.

orinocoWORPIfBSUStatRemoteTxRate.name: orinocoWORPIfBSUStatRemoteTxRate
orinocoWORPIfBSUStatRemoteTxRate.description: This object represents the Transmit Data Rate of the BSU to which the SU is registered.

orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageLocalSignal.name: orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageLocalSignal
orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageLocalSignal.description: The current signal level calculated over all inbound packets. This variable indicates the running average of the SU's local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageLocalNoise.name: orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageLocalNoise
orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageLocalNoise.description: The current noise level calculated over all inbound packets. This variable indicates the running average of the SU's local noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageRemoteSignal.name: orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageRemoteSignal
orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageRemoteSignal.description: The current remote signal level calculated over the inbound packets received at SU, sent by the BSU. This variable indicates the running average of the SU's Rx Signal level(i.e. BSU's Tx Signal level) all registered stations of the remote signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageRemoteNoise.name: orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageRemoteNoise
orinocoWORPIfBSUStatAverageRemoteNoise.description: The current remote noise level calculated over the inbound packets received at SU, sent by the BSU. This variable indicates the running average of the SU's Rx Noise level(i.e. BSU's Tx Noise level) all registered stations of the remote noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriNetworkIPConfigTable.name: oriNetworkIPConfigTable
oriNetworkIPConfigTable.description: This table contains the Network IP configuration for the network interface(s) of the device. For bridge mode, only the address assigned to the Ethernet interface (index 1) will be used.

oriNetworkIPConfigTableEntry.name: oriNetworkIPConfigTableEntry
oriNetworkIPConfigTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry for the network IP configuration for each interface in the system.

oriNetworkIPConfigTableIndex.name: oriNetworkIPConfigTableIndex
oriNetworkIPConfigTableIndex.description: This object represents an index or interface number in the network IP configuration table.

oriNetworkIPConfigIPAddress.name: oriNetworkIPConfigIPAddress
oriNetworkIPConfigIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP Address of the network interface.

oriNetworkIPConfigSubnetMask.name: oriNetworkIPConfigSubnetMask
oriNetworkIPConfigSubnetMask.description: This object represents the subnet mask of the network interface.

oriNetworkIPDefaultRouterIPAddress.name: oriNetworkIPDefaultRouterIPAddress
oriNetworkIPDefaultRouterIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the gateway or router of the device.

oriNetworkIPDefaultTTL.name: oriNetworkIPDefaultTTL
oriNetworkIPDefaultTTL.description: The default value inserted into the Time-To-Live (TTL) field of the IP header of datagrams originated at this entity, whenever a TTL value is not supplied by the transport layer protocol.

oriNetworkIPAddressType.name: oriNetworkIPAddressType
oriNetworkIPAddressType.description: This object identifies if the device is configured to be assigned a static or dynamic IP address using a DHCP client.

oriSNMPReadPassword.name: oriSNMPReadPassword
oriSNMPReadPassword.description: This object represents the read-only community name used in the SNMP protocol. This object is used for reading objects from the SNMP agent. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSNMPReadWritePassword.name: oriSNMPReadWritePassword
oriSNMPReadWritePassword.description: This objecgt represents the read-write community name used in the SNMP protocol. This object is used for reading and writing objects to and from the SNMP Agent. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSNMPAuthorizedManagerCount.name: oriSNMPAuthorizedManagerCount
oriSNMPAuthorizedManagerCount.description: This object reflects the number of entries in the Management IP Access Table.

oriSNMPAccessTable.name: oriSNMPAccessTable
oriSNMPAccessTable.description: This table is used configure management stations that are authorized to manage the device. This table applies to the supported management services/interfaces (SNMP, HTTP, and Telnet). This table is limited to 20 entries.

oriSNMPAccessTableEntry.name: oriSNMPAccessTableEntry
oriSNMPAccessTableEntry.description: This object identifies an entry in the Management IP Access Table.

oriSNMPAccessTableIndex.name: oriSNMPAccessTableIndex
