oriSNMPAccessTableIndex.description: This object represents the index for the Management IP Access Table.

oriSNMPAccessTableIPAddress.name: oriSNMPAccessTableIPAddress
oriSNMPAccessTableIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the management station authorized to manage the device.

oriSNMPAccessTableIPMask.name: oriSNMPAccessTableIPMask
oriSNMPAccessTableIPMask.description: This object represents the IP subnet mask. This object can be used to grant access to a complete subnet.

oriSNMPAccessTableInterfaceBitmask.name: oriSNMPAccessTableInterfaceBitmask
oriSNMPAccessTableInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is used to control the interface access for each table entry in the Management IP Access Table.

oriSNMPAccessTableComment.name: oriSNMPAccessTableComment
oriSNMPAccessTableComment.description: This object is used for an optional comment associated to the Management IP Access Table entry.

oriSNMPAccessTableEntryStatus.name: oriSNMPAccessTableEntryStatus
oriSNMPAccessTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, or create an entry in the Management IP Access Table.

oriSNMPTrapHostTable.name: oriSNMPTrapHostTable
oriSNMPTrapHostTable.description: This table contains the information regarding the trap host that will receive SNMP traps sent by the device. This table is limited 10 entries.

oriSNMPTrapHostTableEntry.name: oriSNMPTrapHostTableEntry
oriSNMPTrapHostTableEntry.description: This object identifies an entry in the SNMP Trap Host Table.

oriSNMPTrapHostTableIndex.name: oriSNMPTrapHostTableIndex
oriSNMPTrapHostTableIndex.description: This object is used as an index for the SNMP Trap Host Table.

oriSNMPTrapHostTableIPAddress.name: oriSNMPTrapHostTableIPAddress
oriSNMPTrapHostTableIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the management station that will receive SNMP Traps from the device.

oriSNMPTrapHostTablePassword.name: oriSNMPTrapHostTablePassword
oriSNMPTrapHostTablePassword.description: This object represents the password that is sent with the SNMP trap messages to allow the host to accept or reject the traps. The trap host will only accept SNMP traps if this password matches the host's password. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSNMPTrapHostTableComment.name: oriSNMPTrapHostTableComment
oriSNMPTrapHostTableComment.description: This object is used for an optional comment associated to the SNMP Trap Host Table entry.

oriSNMPTrapHostTableEntryStatus.name: oriSNMPTrapHostTableEntryStatus
oriSNMPTrapHostTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create an entry in the SNMP Trap Host Table.

oriSNMPInterfaceBitmask.name: oriSNMPInterfaceBitmask
oriSNMPInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is used to control the interface access for SNMP based management (not HTTP and Telnet).

oriSNMPErrorMessage.name: oriSNMPErrorMessage
oriSNMPErrorMessage.description: This object is used to provide additional information in case of an SNMP error.

oriSNMPAccessTableStatus.name: oriSNMPAccessTableStatus
oriSNMPAccessTableStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the Management IP Access Table. If this object is disabled, the check based on source IP address for the enteries in the Management IP Access Table will not be performed.

oriSNMPTrapType.name: oriSNMPTrapType
oriSNMPTrapType.description: This object is used to configure the SNMP trap/notification type that will be generated.

oriSNMPSecureManagementStatus.name: oriSNMPSecureManagementStatus
oriSNMPSecureManagementStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the secure Management feature for the Access Point. With this object enabled, view based access control will be enforced on all forms of management including SNMPv1/v2c, HTTP, WEB, HTTPS, SSH, serial, and Telnet. Also SNMPv3 user security model will be enabled. The default SNMPv3 user is defined as userName 'administrator', with SHA authentication and DES privacy protocols.

oriSNMPV3AuthPassword.name: oriSNMPV3AuthPassword
oriSNMPV3AuthPassword.description: This object represents the SNMPv3 administrator authentication password. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSNMPV3PrivPassword.name: oriSNMPV3PrivPassword
oriSNMPV3PrivPassword.description: This object represents the SNMPv3 administrator privacy password. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriProtocolFilterOperationType.name: oriProtocolFilterOperationType
oriProtocolFilterOperationType.description: This object is used to passthru (allow) or block (deny) packets with protocols in the protocol filter table.

oriProtocolFilterTable.name: oriProtocolFilterTable
oriProtocolFilterTable.description: This table contains the two byte hexadecimal values of the protocols. The packets whose protocol field matches with any of the entries in this table will be forwarded or dropped based on value of oriProtocolFilterFlag. This table is limited to 256 ethernet protocols (enteries).

oriProtocolFilterTableEntry.name: oriProtocolFilterTableEntry
oriProtocolFilterTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the protocol filter table.

oriProtocolFilterTableIndex.name: oriProtocolFilterTableIndex
oriProtocolFilterTableIndex.description: This object is used to index the protocol filter table.

oriProtocolFilterProtocol.name: oriProtocolFilterProtocol
oriProtocolFilterProtocol.description: This object represents a two byte hexadecimal value for the Ethernet protocol to be filtered (the protocol field of the Ethernet packet).

oriProtocolFilterProtocolComment.name: oriProtocolFilterProtocolComment
oriProtocolFilterProtocolComment.description: This object is used as an optional comment for the ethernet protocol to be filtered.

oriProtocolFilterTableEntryStatus.name: oriProtocolFilterTableEntryStatus
oriProtocolFilterTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create the Ethernet protocols in this table.

oriProtocolFilterTableInterfaceBitmask.name: oriProtocolFilterTableInterfaceBitmask
oriProtocolFilterTableInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is isued to control protocol filtering per interface for each entry in this table.

oriProtocolFilterProtocolString.name: oriProtocolFilterProtocolString
oriProtocolFilterProtocolString.description: This object represents the value in the protocol field of the Ethernet packet. The value is of 4-digit Hex format. Example: The value of IP protocol is 0800. The value of ARP protocol is 0806.

oriProtocolFilterInterfaceBitmask.name: oriProtocolFilterInterfaceBitmask
oriProtocolFilterInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is isued to control protocol filtering per interface for the table.

oriAccessControlStatus.name: oriAccessControlStatus
oriAccessControlStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable MAC Access Control feature/filter in the device.

oriAccessControlOperationType.name: oriAccessControlOperationType
oriAccessControlOperationType.description: This flag determines whether the stations with MAC addresses listed in the access control table will be allowed or denied access. This flag is used only if oriAccessControlStatus is enabled. This table is limited to 1000 MAC Address entries.

oriAccessControlTable.name: oriAccessControlTable
oriAccessControlTable.description: This table contains the information about MAC addresses of the wireless stations that are either allowed or disallowed access (based on oriAccessControlOperation) through this device. This table is used only if oriAccessControlStatus is enabled.

oriAccessControlEntry.name: oriAccessControlEntry
oriAccessControlEntry.description: This object represents the entry in the access control table.

oriAccessControlTableIndex.name: oriAccessControlTableIndex
oriAccessControlTableIndex.description: This object is used as an index for the access control table.

oriAccessControlTableMACAddress.name: oriAccessControlTableMACAddress
oriAccessControlTableMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the wireless station that can access the device.

oriAccessControlTableComment.name: oriAccessControlTableComment
oriAccessControlTableComment.description: This object is used as an optional comment associated to the access control table entry.

oriAccessControlTableEntryStatus.name: oriAccessControlTableEntryStatus
oriAccessControlTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create the entries in the Access Control Table.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterTable.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterTable
oriStaticMACAddressFilterTable.description: This table provides the MAC address of the stations on the wired and the wireless interface; the MAC addresses will be given in pairs. Stations listed in the Static MAC Address filter will have no traffic forwarded by the device. This way Multicast traffic exchanged between stations or servers can be prevented, from being transmitted over the wireless medium when both stations are actually located on the wired backbone. This table is limited to 200 entries.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterEntry.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterEntry
oriStaticMACAddressFilterEntry.description: This object identifies the entry in the Static MAC address filter table.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterTableIndex.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterTableIndex
oriStaticMACAddressFilterTableIndex.description: This object is used as an index for the Static MAC address filter table.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterWiredAddress.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterWiredAddress
oriStaticMACAddressFilterWiredAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the station on the wired interface of the device.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterWiredMask.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterWiredMask
oriStaticMACAddressFilterWiredMask.description: This mask determines the presence of wildcard characters in the MAC address of the station on the wired interface. The value F (hex digit) in the mask indicates the presence of a wildcard character and the value 0 indicates its absence.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterWirelessAddress.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterWirelessAddress
oriStaticMACAddressFilterWirelessAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the station on the wireless interface.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterWirelessMask.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterWirelessMask
oriStaticMACAddressFilterWirelessMask.description: The mask that determines the presence of wildcard characters in the MAC address of the station on the wireless side. The value F (hex digit) indicates the presence of a wildcard character and the hex digit 0 indicates its absense.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterTableEntryStatu.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterTableEntryStatus
oriStaticMACAddressFilterTableEntryStatu.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create an entry in the Static MAC Address Table.

oriStaticMACAddressFilterComment.name: oriStaticMACAddressFilterComment
oriStaticMACAddressFilterComment.description: This object is used for an optional comment associated to the access control table entry.

oriBroadcastAddressThreshold.name: oriBroadcastAddressThreshold
oriBroadcastAddressThreshold.description: If broadcast rate from any device (identified by its MAC address) exceeds the limit specified by this value, the device will ignore all subsequent messages issued by the particular network device, or ignore all messages of that type. Valid values for address threshold is between 0 - 255 frames per second. Initial Value is 0 (Disable Storm Threshold Protection).

oriMulticastAddressThreshold.name: oriMulticastAddressThreshold
oriMulticastAddressThreshold.description: If multicast rate from any device (identified by its MAC address) exceeds the limit specified by this value, the device will ignore all subsequent messages issued by the particular network device, or ignore all messages of that type. Valid values for address threshold is between 0 - 255 frames per second. Initial Value is 0 (Disable Storm Threshold Protection).

oriStormThresholdTable.name: oriStormThresholdTable
oriStormThresholdTable.description: The table containing broadcast and multicast threshold values for each interface.

oriStormThresholdTableEntry.name: oriStormThresholdTableEntry
oriStormThresholdTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the storm threshold filter table.

oriStormThresholdIfBroadcast.name: oriStormThresholdIfBroadcast
oriStormThresholdIfBroadcast.description: This parameter specifies a set of Broadcast Storm thresholds for each interface/port of the device, identifying separate values for the number of Broadcast messages/second. Default value is zero, which means disabled.

oriStormThresholdIfMulticast.name: oriStormThresholdIfMulticast
oriStormThresholdIfMulticast.description: This parameter specifies a set of Multicast Storm thresholds for each interface/port of the device, identifying separate values for the number of Multicast messages/second. Default value is zero, which means disabled.

oriPortFilterStatus.name: oriPortFilterStatus
oriPortFilterStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable port filtering.

oriPortFilterOperationType.name: oriPortFilterOperationType
oriPortFilterOperationType.description: This object determines whether the stations with ports listed in the port filter table must be allowed (passthru) or denied (block) to access the device. This object is used only if oriPacketFilterStatus is enabled.

oriPortFilterTable.name: oriPortFilterTable
oriPortFilterTable.description: This table contains the Port number of packets to be filtered. The packets whose port field matches with any of the enabled entries in this table will be blocked (dropped). This table is limited to 256 entries.

oriPortFilterTableEntry.name: oriPortFilterTableEntry
oriPortFilterTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry in the port filter table.

oriPortFilterTableEntryIndex.name: oriPortFilterTableEntryIndex
oriPortFilterTableEntryIndex.description: This object is used as the index for the port filter table. This table supports up to 256 entries.

oriPortFilterTableEntryPort.name: oriPortFilterTableEntryPort
oriPortFilterTableEntryPort.description: This object represents the port number of the packets to be filtered.

oriPortFilterTableEntryPortType.name: oriPortFilterTableEntryPortType
oriPortFilterTableEntryPortType.description: This object specifies the port type.

oriPortFilterTableEntryInterfaceBitmask.name: oriPortFilterTableEntryInterfaceBitmask
oriPortFilterTableEntryInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is used to control port filtering per interface for each entry in the table.

oriPortFilterTableEntryComment.name: oriPortFilterTableEntryComment
oriPortFilterTableEntryComment.description: This object is used for an optional comment associated to the port filter table entry.

oriPortFilterTableEntryStatus.name: oriPortFilterTableEntryStatus
oriPortFilterTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create an entry in the Port Filter Table.

oriBroadcastFilteringTable.name: oriBroadcastFilteringTable
oriBroadcastFilteringTable.description: The table entries for broadcast filters. This table shall contain 5 entries.

oriBroadcastFilteringTableEntry.name: oriBroadcastFilteringTableEntry
oriBroadcastFilteringTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the broadcast filtering table.

oriBroadcastFilteringTableIndex.name: oriBroadcastFilteringTableIndex
oriBroadcastFilteringTableIndex.description: This object represents the index of the Broadcast Filtering table.

oriBroadcastFilteringProtocolName.name: oriBroadcastFilteringProtocolName
oriBroadcastFilteringProtocolName.description: This object represents the broadcast protocol name to be filtered.

oriBroadcastFilteringDirection.name: oriBroadcastFilteringDirection
oriBroadcastFilteringDirection.description: This object represents the direction of the broadcast filter. The filter can be enabled for Ethernet to Wireless, Wireless to Ethernet, or both directions.

oriBroadcastFilteringTableEntryStatus.name: oriBroadcastFilteringTableEntryStatus
oriBroadcastFilteringTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the broadcast filter table enteries.

oriPacketForwardingStatus.name: oriPacketForwardingStatus
oriPacketForwardingStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the Packet Forwarding feature.

oriPacketForwardingMACAddress.name: oriPacketForwardingMACAddress
oriPacketForwardingMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC Address to which all frames will be forwarded by the device.

oriPacketForwardingInterface.name: oriPacketForwardingInterface
oriPacketForwardingInterface.description: This object is used to configure the interface or port that frames will be forwarded to. If this object is not configured, value set to zero, then the bridge will forward the packets on the interface or port the MAC address was learned on. If this object is not configured, value set to zero, and the bridge has not yet learned the MAC address then the frames will be forwarded on all interfaces and ports.

oriIBSSTrafficOperation.name: oriIBSSTrafficOperation
oriIBSSTrafficOperation.description: This object is used to control IntraBSS Traffic. If this object is set to the passthru, then IBSS traffic will be allowed; if this object is set to block, then IBSS traffic will be denied.

oriIntraCellBlockingStatus.name: oriIntraCellBlockingStatus
oriIntraCellBlockingStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable IntraCell Blocking/Filtering.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTable.name: oriIntraCellBlockingMACTable
oriIntraCellBlockingMACTable.description: The MAC table entries for IntraCell Blocking filters. This table can contain up to a maximum of 250 entries.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableEntry.name: oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableEntry
oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableEntry.description: This object represents the entry in the IntraCell Blocking MAC Table.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableIndex.name: oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableIndex
oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index to the IntraCell Blocking MAC Table.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableMACAddress.name: oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableMACAddress
oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the SU which is allowed to communicate with other SUs with the same group ID.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableGroupID1.description: This object is used to activate/deactivate Group ID 1.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableGroupID15.description: This object is used to activate/deactivate Group ID 15.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableGroupID16.description: This object is used to activate/deactivate Group ID 16.

oriIntraCellBlockingMACTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create the entries in the IntraCell Blocking MAC Table.

oriIntraCellBlockingGroupTable.name: oriIntraCellBlockingGroupTable
oriIntraCellBlockingGroupTable.description: The Group table entries for IntraCell Blocking Group IDs. This table can contain a maximum of 16 entries.

oriIntraCellBlockingGroupTableEntry.description: This object represents the entry in the IntraCell Blocking Group Table.

oriIntraCellBlockingGroupTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index to the IntraCell Blocking Group Table.

oriIntraCellBlockingGroupTableName.description: This object represents the group name.

oriIntraCellBlockingGroupTableEntryStatu.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete, create the entries in the IntraCell Blocking Group Table.

oriSecurityGwStatus.name: oriSecurityGwStatus
oriSecurityGwStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the Security Gateway feature.

oriSecurityGwMac.description: This object represents the Security Gateway MAC Address to which all frames will be forwarded by the device.

oriRADIUSClientInvalidServerAddress.name: oriRADIUSClientInvalidServerAddress
oriRADIUSClientInvalidServerAddress.description: This counter represents the total number of RADIUS access-response messages received from an unknown address since system startup.

oriRADIUSMACAccessControl.name: oriRADIUSMACAccessControl
oriRADIUSMACAccessControl.description: This object is used to enables RADIUS Access Control based on wireless stations MAC Address.

oriRADIUSAuthorizationLifeTime.name: oriRADIUSAuthorizationLifeTime
oriRADIUSAuthorizationLifeTime.description: This object represents the authorization lifetime for a certain MAC based RADIUS authenticated client. A value of zero (0) means that re-authorization is disabled. The units for this object is seconds.

oriRADIUSMACAddressFormat.name: oriRADIUSMACAddressFormat
oriRADIUSMACAddressFormat.description: This object is used to configure the MAC Address format that is to be used for communication with the RADIUS Server. Examples of MAC Address Format are: - Dash Delimited: 00-11-22-AA-BB-CC - Colon Delimited: 00:11:22:AA:BB:CC - Single Dash Delimited: 001122-AABBCC - No Delimiter: 001122AABBCC

oriRADIUSLocalUserStatus.name: oriRADIUSLocalUserStatus
oriRADIUSLocalUserStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable local user support when RADIUS based management is enabled.

oriRADIUSLocalUserPassword.name: oriRADIUSLocalUserPassword
oriRADIUSLocalUserPassword.description: This object is the password to access the device when using the local username - root. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriRADIUSbasedManagementAccessProfile.name: oriRADIUSbasedManagementAccessProfile
oriRADIUSbasedManagementAccessProfile.description: This object is used to configure the RADIUS Server profile that will be used for RADIUS based management access. The RADIUS profile is defined in the RADIUS Server Table in the orinocoRADIUSSvrProfile group.

oriRADIUSAuthServerTable.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerTable
oriRADIUSAuthServerTable.description: This table represents the RADIUS servers that the device will communicated with for client authentication. Usually this table should have two members representing the primary and secondary (backup) RADIUS Authentication Servers.

oriRADIUSAuthServerTableEntry.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerTableEntry
oriRADIUSAuthServerTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the RADIUS Authentication Server Table.

oriRADIUSAuthServerTableIndex.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerTableIndex
oriRADIUSAuthServerTableIndex.description: This object is used as an index to the RADIUS Authentication Server Table.

oriRADIUSAuthServerType.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerType
oriRADIUSAuthServerType.description: This object indicates if the RADIUS server will provide Authentication service, Accounting service, or both.

oriRADIUSAuthServerTableEntryStatus.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerTableEntryStatus
oriRADIUSAuthServerTableEntryStatus.description: This object identifies if the RADIUS server entry is enabled or disabled.

oriRADIUSAuthServerIPAddress.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerIPAddress
oriRADIUSAuthServerIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the RADIUS server.

oriRADIUSAuthServerDestPort.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerDestPort
oriRADIUSAuthServerDestPort.description: This object represents the RADIUS server authentication port - the default value is 1812.

oriRADIUSAuthServerSharedSecret.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerSharedSecret
oriRADIUSAuthServerSharedSecret.description: This object represents the shared secret between the RADIUS server and client. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriRADIUSAuthServerResponseTime.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerResponseTime
oriRADIUSAuthServerResponseTime.description: This object represents the time (in seconds) for which the RADIUS client will wait, until another authentication request is sent to the server.

oriRADIUSAuthServerMaximumRetransmission.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerMaximumRetransmission
oriRADIUSAuthServerMaximumRetransmission.description: This object represents the number of retransmissions of authentication requests by the RADIUS Client to the Server.

oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRequests.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRequests
oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRequests.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Requests messages transmitted from the client to the server since client startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRetransmissions.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRetransmissions
oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRetransmissions.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Requests retransmitted by the client to the server since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessAccepts.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessAccepts
oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessAccepts.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS Access Accept messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessChallenges.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessChallenges
oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessChallenges.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Challenges messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRejects.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRejects
oriRADIUSAuthClientAccessRejects.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Rejects messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientMalformedAccessRespon.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientMalformedAccessResponses
oriRADIUSAuthClientMalformedAccessRespon.description: This object represents the number of malformed RADIUS Access Response messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientAuthInvalidAuthentica.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientAuthInvalidAuthenticators
oriRADIUSAuthClientAuthInvalidAuthentica.description: This object represents the number of malformed RADIUS Access Response messages containing invalid authenticators received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientTimeouts.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientTimeouts
oriRADIUSAuthClientTimeouts.description: This object represents the total number of timeouts for RADIUS Access Request messages since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthServerNameOrIPAddress.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerNameOrIPAddress
oriRADIUSAuthServerNameOrIPAddress.description: This object is used to specify the RADIUS Server host name or IP Address.

oriRADIUSAuthServerAddressingFormat.name: oriRADIUSAuthServerAddressingFormat
oriRADIUSAuthServerAddressingFormat.description: This object is used to specify the addressing format for configuring the RADIUS Server. If this object is configured to IP Address, then IP address should be used to specify the server. If this object is configured to name, then the host name should be specified.

oriRADIUSAcctStatus.name: oriRADIUSAcctStatus
oriRADIUSAcctStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the RADIUS Accounting service. This object has been deprecated.

oriRADIUSAcctInactivityTimer.name: oriRADIUSAcctInactivityTimer
oriRADIUSAcctInactivityTimer.description: This parameter represents the inactivity or idle timeout in minutes after which an Accounting Stop request is sent to the RADIUS Accounting server - the default value is 5 minutes. This object has been deprecated.

oriRADIUSAcctServerTable.name: oriRADIUSAcctServerTable
oriRADIUSAcctServerTable.description: This table represents the RADIUS servers that the device will communicated with for accounting. Usually this table should have two members representing the primary and secondary (backup) RADIUS Accounting Servers. This object has been deprecated.

oriRADIUSAcctServerTableEntry.name: oriRADIUSAcctServerTableEntry

oriRADIUSAcctServerSharedSecret.description: This object represents the shared secret between the RADIUS server and client. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks. This object has been deprecated.

oriRADIUSAcctUpdateInterval.description: This object is used to specify the interval in seconds at which RADIUS accounting update messages will be sent. This object has been deprecated.

oriRADIUSSvrTable.name: oriRADIUSSvrTable
oriRADIUSSvrTable.description: This table represents the RADIUS server profile that the device will communicated with for client authentication and/or accounting. oriRADIUSSvrTableEntry.name: oriRADIUSSvrTableEntry
oriRADIUSSvrTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the RADIUS Server Table.

oriRADIUSSvrTableVLANID.description: This object represents the VLAND ID that will be used to tag RADIUS messages from the client to the server.

oriRADIUSSvrTableAuthorizationLifeTime.description: This object represents the authorization lifetime for a certain MAC based RADIUS authenticated client. A value of zero (0) means that re-authorization is disabled. The units for this object is seconds.

oriRADIUSSvrTableAccountingInactivityTim.name: oriRADIUSSvrTableAccountingInactivityTimer
oriRADIUSSvrTableAccountingInactivityTim.description: This parameter represents the client idle timeout in minutes. Once this timer has expired an Accounting Stop request is sent to the RADIUS Accounting Server.

oriRADIUSSvrTableAccountingUpdateInterva.name: oriRADIUSSvrTableAccountingUpdateInterval
oriRADIUSSvrTableAccountingUpdateInterva.description: This object is used to specify the interval in seconds at which RADIUS accounting update messages will be sent. This object is defined in minutes; a value of zero (0) disables the accouting updates.

oriRADIUSSvrTableRowStatus.name: oriRADIUSSvrTableRowStatus
oriRADIUSSvrTableRowStatus.description: This object represents the status of the RADIUS Server profile.

oriRADIUSClientInvalidSvrAddress.name: oriRADIUSClientInvalidSvrAddress
oriRADIUSClientInvalidSvrAddress.description: This counter represents the total number of RADIUS access-response messages received from an unknown address since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTable.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTable
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTable.description: This table is used to store RADIUS Authentication Client Statistics for the configured profiles.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableEntry.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableEntry
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry, primary and secondary/backup, in the RADIUS Authentication Client Statistics table.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableIndex.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableIndex
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableIndex.description: This object is used as an index to the RADIUS Authentication Client Statistics Table.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTablePrimaryOrSec.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTablePrimaryOrSecondaryIndex
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTablePrimaryOrSec.description: This object is used as an secondary index to the RADIUS Authentication Client Statistics Table, which is used to indicate primary and secondary/backup server statistics.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessReques.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessRequests
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessReques.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Requests messages transmitted from the client to the server since client startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessRetran.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessRetransmissions
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessRetran.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Requests retransmitted by the client to the server since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessAccept.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessAccepts
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessAccept.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS Access Accept messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessChalle.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessChallenges
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessChalle.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Challenges messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessReject.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessRejects
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableAccessReject.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Access Rejects messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableMalformedAcc.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableMalformedAccessResponses
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableMalformedAcc.description: This object represents the number of malformed RADIUS Access Response messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableBadAuthentic.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableBadAuthenticators
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableBadAuthentic.description: This object represents the number of malformed RADIUS Access Response messages containing invalid authenticators received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableTimeouts.name: oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableTimeouts
oriRADIUSAuthClientStatTableTimeouts.description: This object represents the total number of timeouts for RADIUS Access Request messages since system startup.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTable.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTable
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTable.description: This table is used to store RADIUS Accounting Client Statistics for the configured profiles.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableEntry.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableEntry
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry, primary and secondary/backup, in the RADIUS Accounting Client Statistics table.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableIndex.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableIndex
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableIndex.description: This object is used as an index to the RADIUS Accounting Client Statistics Table.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTablePrimaryOrSec.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTablePrimaryOrSecondaryIndex
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTablePrimaryOrSec.description: This object is used as an secondary index to the RADIUS Accounting Client Statistics Table, which is used to indicate primary and secondary/backup server statistics.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRe.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRequests
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRe.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Accounting Requests messages transmitted from the client to the server since client startup.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRe.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRetransmissions
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRe.description: This object represents the number of RADIUS Accounting Requests retransmitted by the client to the server since system startup.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRe.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingResponses
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableAccountingRe.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS Accounting Response messages received since system startup.

oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableBadAuthentic.name: oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableBadAuthenticators
oriRADIUSAcctClientStatTableBadAuthentic.description: This object represents the number of malformed RADIUS Access Response messages containing invalid authenticators received since system startup.

oriTelnetSessions.name: oriTelnetSessions
oriTelnetSessions.description: This object is used to enable or disable telnet access and to specify the maximum number of active telnet sessions. When this object is set to 0, telnet access is disabled. When this object is set to something greater than 0, then it specifies the maximum number of active telnet sessions. This object has been deprecated.

oriTelnetPassword.name: oriTelnetPassword
oriTelnetPassword.description: This object is the password to access the device via the telnet interface. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriTelnetPort.name: oriTelnetPort
oriTelnetPort.description: This object represents the TCP/IP port for which the telnet daemon/server will be accessible.

oriTelnetLoginTimeout.name: oriTelnetLoginTimeout
oriTelnetLoginTimeout.description: This object represents the telnet login timeout in seconds.

oriTelnetIdleTimeout.name: oriTelnetIdleTimeout
oriTelnetIdleTimeout.description: This object represents the telnet inactivity/idle timeout in seconds.

oriTelnetInterfaceBitmask.name: oriTelnetInterfaceBitmask
oriTelnetInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is used to control interface access for telnet based management.

oriTelnetSSHStatus.name: oriTelnetSSHStatus
oriTelnetSSHStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable CLI access configuration using secure shell.

oriTelnetSSHHostKeyStatus.name: oriTelnetSSHHostKeyStatus
oriTelnetSSHHostKeyStatus.description: This object is used create or delete the SSH Public Host key of the device.

oriTelnetSSHFingerPrint.name: oriTelnetSSHFingerPrint
oriTelnetSSHFingerPrint.description: This object gives the fingerprint of the SSH Public Host key stored on the device.

oriTelnetRADIUSAccessControl.name: oriTelnetRADIUSAccessControl
oriTelnetRADIUSAccessControl.description: This object is used to enable/disable RADIUS Based Authentication for telnet based management.

oriTFTPServerIPAddress.name: oriTFTPServerIPAddress
oriTFTPServerIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the TFTP server.

oriTFTPFileName.name: oriTFTPFileName
oriTFTPFileName.description: This object represents the filename to upload or download to the TFTP server.

oriTFTPFileType.name: oriTFTPFileType
oriTFTPFileType.description: This object is used for the device to know what type of file is being uploaded or downloaded.

oriTFTPOperation.name: oriTFTPOperation
oriTFTPOperation.description: This object represents the TFTP operation to be executed. The upload function shall transfer the specified file from the device to the TFTP server. The download function shall transfer the specified file from the TFTP server to the device. The download and reboot option, will perform the download and then reboot the device.

oriTFTPFileMode.name: oriTFTPFileMode
oriTFTPFileMode.description: This objects represents the file transfer mode for the TFTP protocol.

oriTFTPOperationStatus.name: oriTFTPOperationStatus
oriTFTPOperationStatus.description: This object represents the TFTP operation status. When a TFTP operation is idle (not in progress) this object will be set to 1. When a TFTP operation is in progress this object will be set to 2. When a TFTP operation has been successful this object will be set to 3. When a TFTP operation has failed this object will be set to 4.

oriTFTPAutoConfigStatus.name: oriTFTPAutoConfigStatus
oriTFTPAutoConfigStatus.description: This objects is used to enable/disable the Auto Configuration feature. This feature allows for a configuration file to be downloaded from a TFTP server so the AP can be configured via a config file.

oriTFTPAutoConfigFilename.name: oriTFTPAutoConfigFilename
oriTFTPAutoConfigFilename.description: This object is used to configure the name of the configuration file to be downloaded using the Auto Configuration feature. This filename can be configured directly via the end user or can be retrieved in the DHCP response message when the AP is configured for dynamic IP address assignment type.

oriTFTPAutoConfigServerIPAddress.name: oriTFTPAutoConfigServerIPAddress
oriTFTPAutoConfigServerIPAddress.description: This object is used to configure the TFTP server IP Address. This object can be configured directly via the end user or can be retrieved in the DHCP response message when the AP is configured for dynamic IP address assignment type.

oriTFTPDowngrade.name: oriTFTPDowngrade
oriTFTPDowngrade.description: On selection of this option, the software will downgrade the configuration file to the specified release from the current release

oriSerialBaudRate.name: oriSerialBaudRate
oriSerialBaudRate.description: This object represents the baud rate for the serial interface - the default value is 9600.

oriSerialDataBits.name: oriSerialDataBits
oriSerialDataBits.description: This object represents the serial interface data bits - the default value is 8.

oriSerialParity.name: oriSerialParity
oriSerialParity.description: This object is used for the serial interface parity check - the default value is none.

oriSerialStopBits.name: oriSerialStopBits
oriSerialStopBits.description: This object indicates the serial interface stop bits - the default value is 1.

oriSerialFlowControl.name: oriSerialFlowControl
oriSerialFlowControl.description: This object is used for the serial interface flow control - the default value is none.

oriIAPPStatus.name: oriIAPPStatus
oriIAPPStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the IAPP feature.

oriIAPPPeriodicAnnounceInterval.name: oriIAPPPeriodicAnnounceInterval
oriIAPPPeriodicAnnounceInterval.description: This object represents interval in seconds for performing an IAPP announce operation by the device.

oriIAPPAnnounceResponseTime.name: oriIAPPAnnounceResponseTime
oriIAPPAnnounceResponseTime.description: This object indicates the amount of time in seconds the device waits to send an IAPP announce response after an announce request message is sent.

oriIAPPHandoverTimeout.name: oriIAPPHandoverTimeout
oriIAPPHandoverTimeout.description: This object represents the time in milliseconds the device waits before it resends a handover response message. This object is originally given in kuseconds, but has been converted to milliseconds.

oriIAPPMaximumHandoverRetransmissions.name: oriIAPPMaximumHandoverRetransmissions
oriIAPPMaximumHandoverRetransmissions.description: This object indicates the maximum amount of retransmission sent by the device for a handover request message.

oriIAPPAnnounceRequestSent.name: oriIAPPAnnounceRequestSent
oriIAPPAnnounceRequestSent.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Announce Request Messages sent since system startup.

oriIAPPAnnounceRequestReceived.name: oriIAPPAnnounceRequestReceived
oriIAPPAnnounceRequestReceived.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Announce Request Messages received since system startup.

oriIAPPAnnounceResponseSent.name: oriIAPPAnnounceResponseSent
oriIAPPAnnounceResponseSent.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Announce Response Messages sent since system startup.

oriIAPPAnnounceResponseReceived.name: oriIAPPAnnounceResponseReceived
oriIAPPAnnounceResponseReceived.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Announce Response Messages received since system startup.

oriIAPPHandoverRequestSent.name: oriIAPPHandoverRequestSent
oriIAPPHandoverRequestSent.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Handover Request messages sent since system startup.

oriIAPPHandoverRequestReceived.name: oriIAPPHandoverRequestReceived
oriIAPPHandoverRequestReceived.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Handover Request messages received since system startup.

oriIAPPHandoverRequestRetransmissions.name: oriIAPPHandoverRequestRetransmissions
oriIAPPHandoverRequestRetransmissions.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Handover Request retransmissions since system startup.

oriIAPPHandoverResponseSent.name: oriIAPPHandoverResponseSent
oriIAPPHandoverResponseSent.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Handover Response messages sent since system startup.

oriIAPPHandoverResponseReceived.name: oriIAPPHandoverResponseReceived
oriIAPPHandoverResponseReceived.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP Handover Response messages received since system startup.

oriIAPPPDUsDropped.name: oriIAPPPDUsDropped
oriIAPPPDUsDropped.description: This object represents the total number of IAPP packets dropped due to erroneous information within the packet since system startup.

oriIAPPRoamingClients.name: oriIAPPRoamingClients
oriIAPPRoamingClients.description: This object represents the total number of client that have roamed from one device to another. This parameter is per device and not a total counter of all the roaming clients for all devices on the network.

oriIAPPMACIPTable.name: oriIAPPMACIPTable
oriIAPPMACIPTable.description: This table contains a list of devices on the network that support IAPP and have the feature enabled.

oriIAPPMACIPTableEntry.name: oriIAPPMACIPTableEntry
oriIAPPMACIPTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the IAPP table, which essentially is a device that supports IAPP and has the feature enabled.

oriIAPPMACIPTableIndex.name: oriIAPPMACIPTableIndex
oriIAPPMACIPTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index for the IAPP MAC-IP table.

oriIAPPMACIPTableSystemName.name: oriIAPPMACIPTableSystemName
oriIAPPMACIPTableSystemName.description: This object represents the System Name of the IAPP enabled device.

oriIAPPMACIPTableIPAddress.name: oriIAPPMACIPTableIPAddress
oriIAPPMACIPTableIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP Address of the IAPP enabled device.

oriIAPPMACIPTableBSSID.name: oriIAPPMACIPTableBSSID
oriIAPPMACIPTableBSSID.description: This object represents the BSSID (MAC address of wireless interface) of the IAPP enabled device.

oriIAPPMACIPTableESSID.name: oriIAPPMACIPTableESSID
oriIAPPMACIPTableESSID.description: This object represents the ESSID (network name) of the IAPP enabled device.

oriIAPPSendAnnounceRequestOnStart.name: oriIAPPSendAnnounceRequestOnStart
oriIAPPSendAnnounceRequestOnStart.description: This object is used to determine whether to send announce request on start.

oriLinkTestTimeOut.name: oriLinkTestTimeOut
oriLinkTestTimeOut.description: The value of this object determines the time (in seconds) that a link test will continue without any SNMP requests for a Link Test Table entry. When the time expires the Link Test Table is cleared.

oriLinkTestInterval.name: oriLinkTestInterval
oriLinkTestInterval.description: This object indicates the interval (in milliseconds) between sending link test frames to a station.

oriLinkTestExplore.name: oriLinkTestExplore
oriLinkTestExplore.description: When this object is set to 2, the device will send out an explore request on all 802.11 interfaces and from the results build the Link Test table. This table is valid only while this object is set to 3.

oriLinkTestTable.name: oriLinkTestTable
oriLinkTestTable.description: This table contains the information for the stations currently associated with the access point.

oriLinkTestTableEntry.name: oriLinkTestTableEntry
oriLinkTestTableEntry.description: This object represents the entry in the Remote Link Test table.

oriLinkTestTableIndex.name: oriLinkTestTableIndex
oriLinkTestTableIndex.description: This object represents a unique value for each station. The value for each station must remain constant at least from one explore to the next.

oriLinkTestInProgress.name: oriLinkTestInProgress
oriLinkTestInProgress.description: When this object is set to 2 the device will initiate a link test sequence with this station.

oriLinkTestStationName.name: oriLinkTestStationName
oriLinkTestStationName.description: This object identifies the name of the station whom which the link test is being performed.

oriLinkTestMACAddress.name: oriLinkTestMACAddress
oriLinkTestMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address that will be mapped to the IP Address of the station.

oriLinkTestStationProfile.name: oriLinkTestStationProfile
oriLinkTestStationProfile.description: This object represents the profile/capabilities for this station.

oriLinkTestOurCurSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurCurSignalLevel
oriLinkTestOurCurSignalLevel.description: The current signal level (in dB) for the link test from this station. This object indicates the running average of the local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriLinkTestOurCurNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurCurNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestOurCurNoiseLevel.description: The current noise level (in dB) for the link test to this station. This object indicates the running average of the local noise level.

oriLinkTestOurCurSNR.name: oriLinkTestOurCurSNR
oriLinkTestOurCurSNR.description: The current signal to noise ratio for the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMinSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMinSignalLevel
oriLinkTestOurMinSignalLevel.description: The minimum signal level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMinNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMinNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestOurMinNoiseLevel.description: The minimum noise level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMinSNR.name: oriLinkTestOurMinSNR
oriLinkTestOurMinSNR.description: The minimum signal to noise ratio during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMaxSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMaxSignalLevel
oriLinkTestOurMaxSignalLevel.description: The maximum signal level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMaxNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMaxNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestOurMaxNoiseLevel.description: The maximum noise level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMaxSNR.name: oriLinkTestOurMaxSNR
oriLinkTestOurMaxSNR.description: The maximum signal to noise ratio during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurLowFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurLowFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurLowFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 1 Mbit/s speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurStandardFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurStandardFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurStandardFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 2 Mbit/s speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMediumFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurMediumFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurMediumFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 5.5 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 5 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurHighFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurHighFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurHighFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 11 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 8 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestHisCurSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisCurSignalLevel
oriLinkTestHisCurSignalLevel.description: The current signal level for the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisCurNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisCurNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestHisCurNoiseLevel.description: The current noise level for the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisCurSNR.name: oriLinkTestHisCurSNR
oriLinkTestHisCurSNR.description: The current signal to noise ratio for the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisMinSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMinSignalLevel
oriLinkTestHisMinSignalLevel.description: The minimum signal level during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisMinNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMinNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestHisMinNoiseLevel.description: The minimum noise level during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisMinSNR.name: oriLinkTestHisMinSNR
oriLinkTestHisMinSNR.description: The minimum signal to noise ratio during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisMaxSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMaxSignalLevel
oriLinkTestHisMaxSignalLevel.description: The maximum signal level during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisMaxNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMaxNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestHisMaxNoiseLevel.description: The maximum noise level during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisMaxSNR.name: oriLinkTestHisMaxSNR
oriLinkTestHisMaxSNR.description: The maximum signal to noise ratio during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisLowFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisLowFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisLowFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 1 Mbit/s speed during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisStandardFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisStandardFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisStandardFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 2 Mbit/s speed during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisMediumFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisMediumFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisMediumFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 5.5 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 5 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestHisHighFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisHighFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisHighFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 11 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 5 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestInterface.name: oriLinkTestInterface
oriLinkTestInterface.description: This object represents the wireless interface number to which the Client has sent the Explore Response Message.

oriLinkTestRadioType.name: oriLinkTestRadioType
oriLinkTestRadioType.description: The Wireless Standard for example IEEE 802.11, 802.11b, 802.11a, or 802.11g being used by the remote station.

oriLinkTestDataRateTable.name: oriLinkTestDataRateTable
oriLinkTestDataRateTable.description: This table contains counters for the data rates for the stations currently associated to the access point.

oriLinkTestDataRateTableEntry.name: oriLinkTestDataRateTableEntry
oriLinkTestDataRateTableEntry.description: This object represents the entry in the Remote Link Test data rate counter table.

oriLinkTestDataRateTableIndex.name: oriLinkTestDataRateTableIndex
oriLinkTestDataRateTableIndex.description: This object is the second index to the Link Test Data Rate Counter Table. The data rates negotiated by the access point and client station will represent an index into this table. The data rates are defined in units of 500 Kbps.

oriLinkTestDataRateTableRemoteCount.name: oriLinkTestDataRateTableRemoteCount
oriLinkTestDataRateTableRemoteCount.description: The total number of frames sent at the data rate value of the index during the link test to the remote station or access point device.

oriLinkTestDataRateTableLocalCount.name: oriLinkTestDataRateTableLocalCount
oriLinkTestDataRateTableLocalCount.description: The total number of frames sent at the data rate value of the index (oriLinkTestDataRateTableindex) during the link test to the client station indenfied by the index (oriLinkTestTableIndex).

oriLinkIntStatus.name: oriLinkIntStatus
oriLinkIntStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the link integrity functionality.

oriLinkIntPollInterval.name: oriLinkIntPollInterval
oriLinkIntPollInterval.description: This object is used to set the poll interval (in milliseconds) for the link integrity check. The valid values for this objects are multiples of 500 milliseconds, a value of zero is not supported.

oriLinkIntPollRetransmissions.name: oriLinkIntPollRetransmissions
oriLinkIntPollRetransmissions.description: This object is used to set the number of retransmissions for the link integrity check.

oriLinkIntTable.name: oriLinkIntTable
oriLinkIntTable.description: This table contains the target IP addresses in order to perform the link integrity check. This table is limited to 5 entries.

oriLinkIntTableEntry.name: oriLinkIntTableEntry
oriLinkIntTableEntry.description: This object identifies the entry in the link integrity target table.

oriLinkIntTableIndex.name: oriLinkIntTableIndex
oriLinkIntTableIndex.description: This object is used as an index for the link integrity target table.

oriLinkIntTableTargetIPAddress.name: oriLinkIntTableTargetIPAddress
oriLinkIntTableTargetIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the target machine for the link integrity check.

oriLinkIntTableComment.name: oriLinkIntTableComment
oriLinkIntTableComment.description: This object is used as an optional comment associated to the link integrity table entry.

oriLinkIntTableEntryStatus.name: oriLinkIntTableEntryStatus
oriLinkIntTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, or delete an entry in the link integrity table.

oriUPSDGPRInterval.name: oriUPSDGPRInterval
oriUPSDGPRInterval.description: This object is used to set the interval of GPR message (in 5ms step), 0 = disable GPR.

oriUPSDMaxActiveSU.name: oriUPSDMaxActiveSU
oriUPSDMaxActiveSU.description: This object is used to set the maximum actived SU per AP.

oriUPSDE911Reserved.name: oriUPSDE911Reserved
oriUPSDE911Reserved.description: This object is used to set the bandwidth allocated for E911calls.

oriUPSDRoamingReserved.name: oriUPSDRoamingReserved
oriUPSDRoamingReserved.description: This object is used to set the bandwidth allocated for roaming SU.

oriQoSPolicyTable.name: oriQoSPolicyTable
oriQoSPolicyTable.description: This table is used to configure Quality of Service policies to be used in the Access Point.

oriQoSPolicyTableEntry.name: oriQoSPolicyTableEntry
oriQoSPolicyTableEntry.description: This object represents entries in the QoS Policy Table.

oriQoSPolicyTableIndex.name: oriQoSPolicyTableIndex
oriQoSPolicyTableIndex.description: This object is used as the primary index to the QoS Policy Table.

oriQoSPolicyTableSecIndex.name: oriQoSPolicyTableSecIndex
oriQoSPolicyTableSecIndex.description: This object is used as the secondary index to the QoS Policy Table.

oriQoSPolicyName.name: oriQoSPolicyName
oriQoSPolicyName.description: This object is used to specify a name for the QoS Policy.

oriQoSPolicyType.name: oriQoSPolicyType
oriQoSPolicyType.description: This object is used to specify the QoS policy type.

oriQoSPolicyPriorityMapping.name: oriQoSPolicyPriorityMapping
oriQoSPolicyPriorityMapping.description: This object is used to configure the QoS priority mapping. The index from either the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table or the index from the 802.1D to IP DSCP mapping table should be specified depending on the policy type. For Layer 2 polices, an index from the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table should be specified. For Layer 3 policies, an index from the QoS 802.1D to IP DSCP mapping table should be specified. If a spectralink policy is configured, then this object is not used.

oriQoSPolicyMarkingStatus.name: oriQoSPolicyMarkingStatus
oriQoSPolicyMarkingStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable QoS markings.

oriQoSPolicyTableRowStatus.name: oriQoSPolicyTableRowStatus
oriQoSPolicyTableRowStatus.description: The object is used to configure the QoS Policy Table row status.

oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTable.name: oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTable
oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTable.description: This table is used to configure Quality of Service mappings between 802.1D and 802.1p priorities.

oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableEntry.name: oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableEntry
oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableEntry.description: This object represents entries in the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p Mapping Table.

oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableIndex.name: oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableIndex
oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableIndex.description: This object is used as the primary index to the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table.

oriQoSDot1dPriority.name: oriQoSDot1dPriority
oriQoSDot1dPriority.description: This object is used to specify the 802.1d priority and is used as the secondary index to the 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table.

oriQoSDot1pPriority.name: oriQoSDot1pPriority
oriQoSDot1pPriority.description: This object is used to specify the 802.1D priority to be mapped to a 802.1p priority.

oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableRowStatus.name: oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableRowStatus
oriQoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableRowStatus.description: The object is used to configure the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table row status.

oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTable.name: oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTable
oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTable.description: This table is used to configure Quality of Service mappings between 802.1D to IP DSCP priorities.

oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableEntry.name: oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableEntry
oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableEntry.description: This object represents entries in the 802.1D to IP DSCP Mapping Table.

oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableIndex.name: oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableIndex
oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableIndex.description: This object is used as the primary index to the 802.1D to IP DSCP mapping table.

oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPPriority.name: oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPPriority
oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPPriority.description: This object is used to specify the 802.1D priority and is used as the secondary index to the 802.1D to IP DSCP mapping table.

oriQoSIPDSCPLowerLimit.name: oriQoSIPDSCPLowerLimit
oriQoSIPDSCPLowerLimit.description: This object is used to specify IP DSCP lower limit.

oriQoSIPDSCPUpperLimit.name: oriQoSIPDSCPUpperLimit
oriQoSIPDSCPUpperLimit.description: This object is used to specify IP DSCP upper limit.

oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableRowStatus.name: oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableRowStatus
oriQoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableRowStatus.description: The object is used to configure the 802.1D to IP DSCP mapping table row status.

oriDHCPServerStatus.name: oriDHCPServerStatus
oriDHCPServerStatus.description: This object indicates if the DHCP server is enabled or disabled in the device.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTable.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTable
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTable.description: This table contains the pools of IP Addresses that the DHCP server will assign to the DHCP clients. This table is limited to 20.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEntry.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEntry
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEntry.description: This object represents entries in the DHCP IP Address Pool Table.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableIndex.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableIndex
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index for the IP Address Pool table.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableStartIPAddress.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableStartIPAddress
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableStartIPAddress.description: This object represents the start IP address for this DHCP IP Address IP Pool Table entry.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEndIPAddress.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEndIPAddress
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEndIPAddress.description: This object represents the end IP address for this DHCP IP Address IP Pool Table entry.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableWidth.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableWidth
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableWidth.description: This object represents the width or number of IP Address in the DHCP IP Address Pool table entry.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableDefaultLeaseTime.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableDefaultLeaseTime
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableDefaultLeaseTime.description: This object represents the default lease time, in seconds, for the IP address assigned by the DHCP server to the DHCP client.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableMaximumLeaseTime.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableMaximumLeaseTime
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableMaximumLeaseTime.description: This object represents the maximum lease time in seconds for the IP address assigned by the DHCP server to the DHCP client.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableComment.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableComment
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableComment.description: This object represents an optional comment for this table entry.

oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEntryStatus.name: oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEntryStatus
oriDHCPServerIPPoolTableEntryStatus.description: The object indicates the status of the DHCP IP Address Pool Table entry.

oriDHCPServerDefaultGatewayIPAddress.name: oriDHCPServerDefaultGatewayIPAddress
oriDHCPServerDefaultGatewayIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP Address of the gateway or router that the DHCP Server will assign to the DHCP client.

oriDHCPServerSubnetMask.name: oriDHCPServerSubnetMask
oriDHCPServerSubnetMask.description: This object represents the subnet mask to be provided to DHCP clients. This object is the same as the subnet mask for the device.

oriDHCPServerNumIPPoolTableEntries.name: oriDHCPServerNumIPPoolTableEntries
oriDHCPServerNumIPPoolTableEntries.description: This object represents the number of entries in the DHCP IP Address Pool Table.

oriDHCPServerPrimaryDNSIPAddress.name: oriDHCPServerPrimaryDNSIPAddress
oriDHCPServerPrimaryDNSIPAddress.description: This object represents the primary DNS Server IP Address to be assinged to a DHCP Client.

oriDHCPServerSecondaryDNSIPAddress.name: oriDHCPServerSecondaryDNSIPAddress
oriDHCPServerSecondaryDNSIPAddress.description: This object represents the secondary DNS Server IP Address to be assinged to a DHCP Client.

oriDHCPClientID.name: oriDHCPClientID
oriDHCPClientID.description: This object represents the DHCP client ID.

oriDHCPClientInterfaceBitmask.name: oriDHCPClientInterfaceBitmask
oriDHCPClientInterfaceBitmask.description: This object indicates to which interface a DHCP Request in sent when the unit is in routing mode

oriDHCPRelayStatus.name: oriDHCPRelayStatus
oriDHCPRelayStatus.description: This object is used to enable and disable the DHCP Relay functionality.

oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTable.name: oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTable
oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTable.description: This table contains a list of DHCP servers to which the DHCP Agent will communicate with.

oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableEntry.name: oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableEntry
oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableEntry.description: This object represents and entry in the DHCP Server table.

oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableIndex.name: oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableIndex
oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index to this table. This table is limited to 10 entries.

oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableIpAddress.name: oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableIpAddress
oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableIpAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the DHCP server that shall receive DHCP requests from the device.

oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableComment.name: oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableComment
oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableComment.description: This object represents an optional comment in order to provide additional information or a unique identifier for the DHCP server (for example the server system name).

oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableEntryStatus.name: oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableEntryStatus
oriDHCPRelayDHCPServerTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, delete or create an entry in the DHCP Server Table.

oriHTTPInterfaceBitmask.name: oriHTTPInterfaceBitmask
oriHTTPInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is used to control interface access for HTTP based management.

oriHTTPPassword.name: oriHTTPPassword
oriHTTPPassword.description: This object represents the login password in order to manage the device via a standard web browser. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriHTTPPort.name: oriHTTPPort
oriHTTPPort.description: This object represents the TCP/IP port by which the HTTP server will be accessible.

oriHTTPWebSitenameTable.name: oriHTTPWebSitenameTable
oriHTTPWebSitenameTable.description: This table is used to store the different website interfaces stored in the device. Different interfaces can be used to support multiple languages, user levels (novice, expert), etc.

oriHTTPWebSitenameTableEntry.name: oriHTTPWebSitenameTableEntry
oriHTTPWebSitenameTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry is the HTTP website name table.

oriHTTPWebSitenameTableIndex.name: oriHTTPWebSitenameTableIndex
oriHTTPWebSitenameTableIndex.description: This objects represents the index to the website interface table.

oriHTTPWebSiteFilename.name: oriHTTPWebSiteFilename
oriHTTPWebSiteFilename.description: This object represents the filename under which the website interface is stored in the device.

oriHTTPWebSiteLanguage.name: oriHTTPWebSiteLanguage
oriHTTPWebSiteLanguage.description: This object represents the language of the website interface.

oriHTTPWebSiteDescription.name: oriHTTPWebSiteDescription
oriHTTPWebSiteDescription.description: This object provides a description for the website interface.

oriHTTPWebSitenameTableStatus.name: oriHTTPWebSitenameTableStatus
oriHTTPWebSitenameTableStatus.description: This object is used to enable, disable, or delete a website interface file.

oriHTTPRefreshDelay.name: oriHTTPRefreshDelay
oriHTTPRefreshDelay.description: This object is used for the automatic refresh delay for the website pages.

oriHTTPHelpInformationLink.name: oriHTTPHelpInformationLink
oriHTTPHelpInformationLink.description: This object is used to configure the link in the web interface for where help information can be retrieved.

oriHTTPSSLStatus.name: oriHTTPSSLStatus
oriHTTPSSLStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable SSL on HTTP based management.

oriHTTPSSLPassphrase.name: oriHTTPSSLPassphrase
oriHTTPSSLPassphrase.description: This object is used to specify the SSL certificate passphrase on HTTP based management. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriHTTPSetupWizardStatus.name: oriHTTPSetupWizardStatus
oriHTTPSetupWizardStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the HTT setup wizard. The user can manually disable this functionality or when the setup wizard completes it process successfully it sets this object to disable.

oriHTTPRADIUSAccessControl.name: oriHTTPRADIUSAccessControl
oriHTTPRADIUSAccessControl.description: This object is used to enable/disable RADIUS Based Authentication for HTTP based management.

oriWDSSetupTable.name: oriWDSSetupTable
oriWDSSetupTable.description: This table is used in to configure the WDS feature in the device.

oriWDSSetupTableEntry.name: oriWDSSetupTableEntry
oriWDSSetupTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the WDS table. Note this table is index by ifIndex and WDS table index.

oriWDSSetupTablePortIndex.name: oriWDSSetupTablePortIndex
oriWDSSetupTablePortIndex.description: This object represents the WDS port number.

oriWDSSetupTableEntryStatus.name: oriWDSSetupTableEntryStatus
oriWDSSetupTableEntryStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable a WDS table entry (link).

oriWDSSetupTablePartnerMACAddress.name: oriWDSSetupTablePartnerMACAddress
oriWDSSetupTablePartnerMACAddress.description: This object represents the partner MAC address for a WDS table entry (link).

oriWDSSecurityTable.name: oriWDSSecurityTable
oriWDSSecurityTable.description: This table is used in to configure the WDS security modes for all entries in the WDS table.

oriWDSSecurityTableEntry.name: oriWDSSecurityTableEntry
oriWDSSecurityTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the WDS security table. Note this table is index by ifIndex since the security configuration will apply for all the WDS links per interface.

oriWDSSecurityTableSecurityMode.name: oriWDSSecurityTableSecurityMode
oriWDSSecurityTableSecurityMode.description: This object is used to configure the WDS security mode. Currently the supported WDS security modes are none and wep.

oriWDSSecurityTableEncryptionKey0.name: oriWDSSecurityTableEncryptionKey0
oriWDSSecurityTableEncryptionKey0.description: This object represents the WDS Encryption Key 0. When the WDS security mode is configured to wep, this object must be configured to a valid value. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriGenericTrapVariable.name: oriGenericTrapVariable
oriGenericTrapVariable.description: This object is used to provide additional information on traps.

oriTrapVarMACAddress.name: oriTrapVarMACAddress
oriTrapVarMACAddress.description: This object is used to store the MAC address of the device that has sent a trap.

oriTrapVarTFTPIPAddress.name: oriTrapVarTFTPIPAddress
oriTrapVarTFTPIPAddress.description: This object is used to store the IP Address of the TFTP server.

oriTrapVarTFTPFilename.name: oriTrapVarTFTPFilename
oriTrapVarTFTPFilename.description: This object is used to store the name of the file on which the TFTP operation has occurred.

oriTrapVarTFTPOperation.name: oriTrapVarTFTPOperation
oriTrapVarTFTPOperation.description: This object is used to store the TFTP operation that failed, either download or upload.

oriTrapVarUnauthorizedManagerIPaddress.name: oriTrapVarUnauthorizedManagerIPaddress
oriTrapVarUnauthorizedManagerIPaddress.description: This object is used to store the IP address of the unauthorized manager that has attempted to manage the device.

oriTrapVarFailedAuthenticationType.name: oriTrapVarFailedAuthenticationType
oriTrapVarFailedAuthenticationType.description: This trap variable is used to specify the client authentication method/type that failed. The authentication methods/types are dependant on the device and can range from the following: - MAC Access Control Table - RADIUS MAC Authentication - 802.1x Authentication specifying the EAP-Type - WORP Mutual Authentication - SSID Authorization Failure specifying the SSID - VLAN ID Authorization Failure specifying the VLAN ID

oriTrapVarUnAuthorizedManagerCount.name: oriTrapVarUnAuthorizedManagerCount
oriTrapVarUnAuthorizedManagerCount.description: This object represents a counter for the number of unauthorized SNMP managers that have attempted to modify and/or view the devices setup. When this number is incremented a trap should be sent out notifying the trap host(s) that an unauthorized station has attempted to configure or monitor the device the count should also be sent out in the trap message.

oriTrapVarTaskSuspended.name: oriTrapVarTaskSuspended
oriTrapVarTaskSuspended.description: This object is used to inform what task has been suspended on the device.

oriTrapVarUnauthorizedClientMACAddress.name: oriTrapVarUnauthorizedClientMACAddress
oriTrapVarUnauthorizedClientMACAddress.description: This object is used to store the MAC Address of an unauthorized client station.

oriTrapVarWirelessCard.name: oriTrapVarWirelessCard
oriTrapVarWirelessCard.description: This object is used to determine on which Wireless Card, PC Card A or PC Card B, a wireless TRAP has occured on.

oriTrapVarInterface.name: oriTrapVarInterface
oriTrapVarInterface.description: This object is used to store the interface number.

oriTrapVarBatchCLIFilename.name: oriTrapVarBatchCLIFilename
oriTrapVarBatchCLIFilename.description: This object is used to store filename used for Batch CLI execution.

oriTrapVarBatchCLIMessage.name: oriTrapVarBatchCLIMessage
oriTrapVarBatchCLIMessage.description: This object is used to store message from Batch CLI execution.

oriTrapVarBatchCLILineNumber.name: oriTrapVarBatchCLILineNumber
oriTrapVarBatchCLILineNumber.description: This object is used to store line number of command executed in Batch CLI.

oriTrapVarDHCPServerIPAddress.name: oriTrapVarDHCPServerIPAddress
oriTrapVarDHCPServerIPAddress.description: This object is used to store the DHCP Server IP Address from which the access point has received an IP address as a result of the a DHCP client request.

oriTrapVarIPAddress.name: oriTrapVarIPAddress
oriTrapVarIPAddress.description: This object is a trap variable/object to store an IP address.

oriTrapVarSubnetMask.name: oriTrapVarSubnetMask
oriTrapVarSubnetMask.description: This object is a trap variable/object to store a subnet mask.

oriTrapVarDefaultRouterIPAddress.name: oriTrapVarDefaultRouterIPAddress
oriTrapVarDefaultRouterIPAddress.description: This object is a trap variable/object to store a default router or gateway IP address.

oriConfigurationTrapsStatus.name: oriConfigurationTrapsStatus
oriConfigurationTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the configuration related traps.

oriSecurityTrapsStatus.name: oriSecurityTrapsStatus
oriSecurityTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the security related traps.

oriWirelessIfTrapsStatus.name: oriWirelessIfTrapsStatus
oriWirelessIfTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the wireless interface/card related traps.

oriOperationalTrapsStatus.name: oriOperationalTrapsStatus
oriOperationalTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the operational related traps.

oriFlashMemoryTrapsStatus.name: oriFlashMemoryTrapsStatus
oriFlashMemoryTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the flash memory related traps.

oriTFTPTrapsStatus.name: oriTFTPTrapsStatus
oriTFTPTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the TFTP related traps.

oriTrapsImageStatus.name: oriTrapsImageStatus
oriTrapsImageStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the Image related traps.

oriADSLIfTrapsStatus.name: oriADSLIfTrapsStatus
oriADSLIfTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the ADSL interface related traps.

oriWORPTrapsStatus.name: oriWORPTrapsStatus
oriWORPTrapsStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the WORP related traps.

oriProxyARPStatus.name: oriProxyARPStatus
oriProxyARPStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the Proxy ARP functionality in the device.

oriIPARPFilteringStatus.name: oriIPARPFilteringStatus
oriIPARPFilteringStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the IP/ARP functionality in the device.

oriIPARPFilteringIPAddress.name: oriIPARPFilteringIPAddress
oriIPARPFilteringIPAddress.description: This object is used to specify the IP/ARP Filtering address in the device.

oriIPARPFilteringSubnetMask.name: oriIPARPFilteringSubnetMask
oriIPARPFilteringSubnetMask.description: This object is used to specify the IP/ARP Subnet Mask in the device.

oriSpanningTreeStatus.name: oriSpanningTreeStatus
oriSpanningTreeStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the spanning tree protocol in the device.

oriSecurityConfiguration.name: oriSecurityConfiguration
oriSecurityConfiguration.description: This object represents the supported security configuration options. This object has been deprecated.

oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLengthTable.name: oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLengthTable
oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLengthTable.description: This table is used to specify the encryption key length for the wireless interface(s). This table has been deprecated.

oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLengthTableEntry.name: oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLengthTableEntry
oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLengthTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the encryption key length table. This object has been deprecated.

oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLength.name: oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLength
oriSecurityEncryptionKeyLength.description: This object represents the encryption key length, the supported key lengths are 64 bits (40 + 24 for IV), and 128 bits (104 + 24 for IV). This object has been deprecated.

oriSecurityRekeyingInterval.name: oriSecurityRekeyingInterval
oriSecurityRekeyingInterval.description: This object represents the encryption rekeying interval in seconds. This object has been deprecated.

oriRADStatus.name: oriRADStatus
oriRADStatus.description: This object allows to enable or disable the RAD service in the device.

oriRADInterval.name: oriRADInterval
oriRADInterval.description: This object is used to identify the interval at which the RAD feature will initialize. The units of this object is minutes.

oriRADInterfaceBitmask.name: oriRADInterfaceBitmask
oriRADInterfaceBitmask.description: This object is used to configure the interface(s) on which the RAD feature will operate on.

oriRADLastSuccessfulScanTime.name: oriRADLastSuccessfulScanTime
oriRADLastSuccessfulScanTime.description: This object is the number of seconds that have elapsed since the last successful RAD scan since the AP has started up.

oriRADAccessPointCount.name: oriRADAccessPointCount
oriRADAccessPointCount.description: This object represents the number of access points that were discovered since the last RAD scan.

oriRADScanResultsTable.name: oriRADScanResultsTable
oriRADScanResultsTable.description: This table is used to store the RAD scan results. Each entry represents an access point scanned in the network.

oriRADScanResultsTableEntry.name: oriRADScanResultsTableEntry
