oriRADScanResultsTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the RAD scan results table.

oriRADScanResultsTableIndex.name: oriRADScanResultsTableIndex
oriRADScanResultsTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index to the scan results table.

oriRADScanResultsMACAddress.name: oriRADScanResultsMACAddress
oriRADScanResultsMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the access point detected during a RAD scan.

oriRADScanResultsFrequencyChannel.name: oriRADScanResultsFrequencyChannel
oriRADScanResultsFrequencyChannel.description: This object represents the frequency channel of the access point.

oriRogueScanConfigTable.name: oriRogueScanConfigTable
oriRogueScanConfigTable.description: This table is used to configure the Rogue Scan feature per wireless network interface card.

oriRogueScanConfigTableEntry.name: oriRogueScanConfigTableEntry
oriRogueScanConfigTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the Rogue Scan Config Table.

oriRogueScanConfigTableScanMode.name: oriRogueScanConfigTableScanMode
oriRogueScanConfigTableScanMode.description: This object is used to configure the scan mode for the wireless NIC.

oriRogueScanConfigTableScanCycleTime.name: oriRogueScanConfigTableScanCycleTime
oriRogueScanConfigTableScanCycleTime.description: This object is used to configure the rogue scan cycle time for the wireless NIC.

oriRogueScanConfigTableScanStatus.name: oriRogueScanConfigTableScanStatus
oriRogueScanConfigTableScanStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable rogue scan on the wireless NIC.

oriRogueScanStationCountWirelessCardA.name: oriRogueScanStationCountWirelessCardA
oriRogueScanStationCountWirelessCardA.description: This object represents the number of stations that were discovered/detected on the device's wireless NIC A.

oriRogueScanStationCountWirelessCardB.name: oriRogueScanStationCountWirelessCardB
oriRogueScanStationCountWirelessCardB.description: This object represents the number of stations that were discovered/detected on the device's wireless NIC B.

oriRogueScanResultsTableAgingTime.name: oriRogueScanResultsTableAgingTime
oriRogueScanResultsTableAgingTime.description: This object represents the aging time for the entries in RogueScanResultsTable, after which the entries are removed from RogueScanResultsTable.

oriRogueScanResultsTableClearEntries.name: oriRogueScanResultsTableClearEntries
oriRogueScanResultsTableClearEntries.description: This object is used to remove the content/entries of RogueScanResultsTable. When this object is set, the content of the table shall be cleared.

oriRogueScanResultsNotificationMode.name: oriRogueScanResultsNotificationMode
oriRogueScanResultsNotificationMode.description: This object is used to configure the trap/notification mode for detected stations during Rogue Scan.

oriRogueScanResultsTrapReportType.name: oriRogueScanResultsTrapReportType
oriRogueScanResultsTrapReportType.description: This object is used to configure the trap/notification report type for detected stations during Rogue Scan.

oriRogueScanResultsTable.name: oriRogueScanResultsTable
oriRogueScanResultsTable.description: This table is used to store the rogue scan results. Each entry represents a rogue wireless station detected in the network.

oriRogueScanResultsTableEntry.name: oriRogueScanResultsTableEntry
oriRogueScanResultsTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the rogue scan results table.

oriRogueScanResultsTableIndex.name: oriRogueScanResultsTableIndex
oriRogueScanResultsTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index to the rogue scan results table.

oriRogueScanResultsStationType.name: oriRogueScanResultsStationType
oriRogueScanResultsStationType.description: This object represents the type of station detected during a rogue scan.

oriRogueScanResultsMACAddress.name: oriRogueScanResultsMACAddress
oriRogueScanResultsMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the station detected during a rogue scan.

oriRogueScanResultsFrequencyChannel.name: oriRogueScanResultsFrequencyChannel
oriRogueScanResultsFrequencyChannel.description: This object represents the frequency channel on which the rogue wireless stations was detected.

oriRogueScanResultsSNR.name: oriRogueScanResultsSNR
oriRogueScanResultsSNR.description: This object represents the signal to noise ration (SNR) for the station detected during a rogue scan.

oriRogueScanResultsBSSID.name: oriRogueScanResultsBSSID
oriRogueScanResultsBSSID.description: This object represents BSSID of the station detected during a rogue scan.

oriSecurityConfigTable.name: oriSecurityConfigTable
oriSecurityConfigTable.description: This table is used to specify the security configuration for the wireless interface(s) in the access point.

oriSecurityConfigTableEntry.name: oriSecurityConfigTableEntry
oriSecurityConfigTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the security configuration table.

oriSecurityConfigTableSupportedSecurityM.name: oriSecurityConfigTableSupportedSecurityModes
oriSecurityConfigTableSupportedSecurityM.description: This object is used to provide information on the supported security modes by the wireless interface(s). The possible security modes can be: - None: no security mode enabled. - dot1x: 802.1x authentication enabled. - mixed: mixed WEP and 802.1x. - wpa: WiFi Protected Access enabled. - wpa-psk: WiFi Protected Access with Preshared Keys enabled.

oriSecurityConfigTableSecurityMode.name: oriSecurityConfigTableSecurityMode
oriSecurityConfigTableSecurityMode.description: This object is used to configure the security mode. The supported security modes are: - None: no security mode enabled. - dot1x: 802.1x authentication enabled. - mixed: mixed WEP and 802.1x. - wpa: WiFi Protected Access enabled. - wpa-psk: WiFi Protected Access with Preshared Keys enabled.

oriSecurityConfigTableRekeyingInterval.name: oriSecurityConfigTableRekeyingInterval
oriSecurityConfigTableRekeyingInterval.description: This object represents the encryption rekeying interval in seconds.

oriSecurityConfigTableEncryptionKeyLengt.name: oriSecurityConfigTableEncryptionKeyLength
oriSecurityConfigTableEncryptionKeyLengt.description: This object represents the encryption key length, the supported key lengths are 64 bits (40 + 24 for IV), 128 bits (104 + 24 for IV), and 152 bits (128 + 24 for IV).

oriSecurityHwConfigResetStatus.name: oriSecurityHwConfigResetStatus
oriSecurityHwConfigResetStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the status of configuration reset using the hardware reset button.

oriSecurityHwConfigResetPassword.name: oriSecurityHwConfigResetPassword
oriSecurityHwConfigResetPassword.description: This object represents the configuration reset password. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSecurityProfileTable.name: oriSecurityProfileTable
oriSecurityProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure a security profile. A security profile can consist of single or muliple security modes.

oriSecurityProfileTableEntry.name: oriSecurityProfileTableEntry
oriSecurityProfileTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the security profile table. This table is index by two indices - the first/primary index defines the security profile, the second index defines a single or multiple security policies per profile. The primary index is used in the wireless interface SSID table to specify which security profile to use per SSID. The admin/user can configure policies for different wireless station types by specifying a authentication and cipher mode/type. Below are examples of how to configure different STA types. STA Type Authentication Mode Cipher Mode ======== =================== =========== Non Secure None None WEP None WEP (64, 128, 152) 802.1x 802.1x WEP (64, 128) WPA 802.1x TKIP WPA-PSK PSK TKIP 802.11i 802.1x AES 802.11i-PSK PSK AES In the case of None, WEP, WPA-PSK, and 802.11i-PSK, MAC Access Control Table/List and RADIUS based MAC access control can be used to authenticate the wireless STA.

oriSecurityProfileTableIndex.name: oriSecurityProfileTableIndex
oriSecurityProfileTableIndex.description: This object represents the primary index of the Security Policy Table. This index is used to specify which security policy will be used per SSID, in the Wireless Interface SSID Table. A security policy can consist of a single or multiple security modes.

oriSecurityProfileTableSecModeIndex.name: oriSecurityProfileTableSecModeIndex
oriSecurityProfileTableSecModeIndex.description: This object is the secondary index to the Security Policy Table. This index will represent the different security modes per security profile.

oriSecurityProfileTableAuthenticationMod.name: oriSecurityProfileTableAuthenticationMode
oriSecurityProfileTableAuthenticationMod.description: This object is used to specify the authentication mode for the security mode.

oriSecurityProfileTableCipherMode.name: oriSecurityProfileTableCipherMode
oriSecurityProfileTableCipherMode.description: This object is used to specify the cipher mode/type for the security mode.

oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey0.name: oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey0
oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey0.description: This object represents Encryption Key 0. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey1.name: oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey1
oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey1.description: This object represents Encryption Key 1. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey2.name: oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey2
oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey2.description: This object represents Encryption Key 2. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey3.name: oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey3
oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKey3.description: This object represents Encryption Key 3. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionTxKey.name: oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionTxKey
oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionTxKey.description: This object indicates which encryption key is used to encrypt data that is sent via the wireless interfaces. The default value for this object should be key 0.

oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKeyLeng.name: oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKeyLength
oriSecurityProfileTableEncryptionKeyLeng.description: This object represents the encryption key length, the supported key lengths are 64 bits (40 + 24 for IV), 128 bits (104 + 24 for IV), and 152 bits (128 + 24 for IV).

oriSecurityProfileTablePSKValue.name: oriSecurityProfileTablePSKValue
oriSecurityProfileTablePSKValue.description: The Pre-Shared Key (PSK) for when RSN in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite. In that case, the PMK will obtain its value from this object. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

oriSecurityProfileTablePSKPassPhrase.name: oriSecurityProfileTablePSKPassPhrase
oriSecurityProfileTablePSKPassPhrase.description: The PSK, for when RSN in PSK mode is the selected authentication suite, is configured by oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKValue. An alternative manner of setting the PSK uses the password-to-key algorithm defined in the standard. This variable provides a means to enter a pass phrase. When this object is written, the RSN entity shall use the password-to-key algorithm specified in the standard to derive a pre-shared and populate oriWirelessIfSSIDTablePSKValue with this key. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

oriSecurityProfileTableStatus.name: oriSecurityProfileTableStatus
oriSecurityProfileTableStatus.description: This object represents the Table row status.

oriSecurityProfileFourWEPKeySupport.name: oriSecurityProfileFourWEPKeySupport
oriSecurityProfileFourWEPKeySupport.description: This object is used to configure the security profile to use with four WEP keys. Currently only one security profile can be active which supports four WEP keys. Therefore this object is used to specify which profile will be using four WEP keys. The purpose of this object is to support legacy products/users that are still using four WEP keys.

oriPPPoEStatus.name: oriPPPoEStatus
oriPPPoEStatus.description: This object allows to enable or disable the PPPoE service in the device.

oriPPPoEMaximumNumberOfSessions.name: oriPPPoEMaximumNumberOfSessions
oriPPPoEMaximumNumberOfSessions.description: This object represents the maximum number of PPPoE sessions.

oriPPPoENumberOfActiveSessions.name: oriPPPoENumberOfActiveSessions
oriPPPoENumberOfActiveSessions.description: This object represents the number of active PPPoE sessions.

oriPPPoESessionTable.name: oriPPPoESessionTable
oriPPPoESessionTable.description: This table is used to configure the PPPoE session information.

oriPPPoESessionTableEntry.name: oriPPPoESessionTableEntry
oriPPPoESessionTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the PPPoE session table.

oriPPPoESessionTableIndex.name: oriPPPoESessionTableIndex
oriPPPoESessionTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index to the PPPoE Session Table.

oriPPPoESessionWANConnectMode.name: oriPPPoESessionWANConnectMode
oriPPPoESessionWANConnectMode.description: This object represents the WAN connect mode.

oriPPPoESessionIdleTimeOut.name: oriPPPoESessionIdleTimeOut
oriPPPoESessionIdleTimeOut.description: This object is used as a timeout for the PPPoE session to be disconnected from public side if idle for specified amount of time.

oriPPPoESessionConnectTime.name: oriPPPoESessionConnectTime
oriPPPoESessionConnectTime.description: This object identifies the PPPoE session connect time.

oriPPPoESessionConnectTimeLimitation.name: oriPPPoESessionConnectTimeLimitation
oriPPPoESessionConnectTimeLimitation.description: This object represents the maximum connection time per session.

oriPPPoESessionConfigPADITxInterval.name: oriPPPoESessionConfigPADITxInterval
oriPPPoESessionConfigPADITxInterval.description: This object represents the time in seconds between PADI retries from the Host.

oriPPPoESessionConfigPADIMaxNumberOfRetr.name: oriPPPoESessionConfigPADIMaxNumberOfRetries
oriPPPoESessionConfigPADIMaxNumberOfRetr.description: This object represents the number of times the Host sends a PADI.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberPADITx.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberPADITx
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberPADITx.description: This object represents the number of PPPoE PADI transmitted.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberPADTTx.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberPADTTx
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberPADTTx.description: This object represents the number of PPPoE PADT transmitted.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberServiceName.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberServiceNameErrors
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberServiceName.description: This object represents the number of PPPoE Service-Name-Error tags received/transmitted.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberACSystemErr.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberACSystemErrors
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberACSystemErr.description: This object represents the number of PPPoE AC-System-Error tags received/transmitted.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberGenericErro.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberGenericErrorsRx
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberGenericErro.description: This object represents the number of PPPoE Generic-Error tags received.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberGenericErro.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberGenericErrorsTx
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberGenericErro.description: This object represents the number of PPPoE Generic Error tags transmitted.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberMalformedPa.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberMalformedPackets
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberMalformedPa.description: This object represents teh number of malformed PPPoE packets received.

oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberMultiplePAD.name: oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberMultiplePADORx
oriPPPoESessionBindingsNumberMultiplePAD.description: This object represents the number of PPPoE multiple PADO's received after a PADI request.

oriPPPoESessionUserName.name: oriPPPoESessionUserName
oriPPPoESessionUserName.description: This object represents the PPPoE user name.

oriPPPoESessionUserNamePassword.name: oriPPPoESessionUserNamePassword
oriPPPoESessionUserNamePassword.description: This object represents the PPPoE user name password. This object should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

oriPPPoESessionServiceName.name: oriPPPoESessionServiceName
oriPPPoESessionServiceName.description: This object represents the PPPoE service name.

oriPPPoESessionISPName.name: oriPPPoESessionISPName
oriPPPoESessionISPName.description: This object represents the PPPoE ISP name.

oriPPPoESessionTableStatus.name: oriPPPoESessionTableStatus
oriPPPoESessionTableStatus.description: This object represents the PPPoE ISP table entry status.

oriPPPoESessionWANManualConnect.name: oriPPPoESessionWANManualConnect
oriPPPoESessionWANManualConnect.description: This object is used to connect of disconnect the PPPoE session when the connect mode is set to manual.

oriPPPoESessionWANConnectionStatus.name: oriPPPoESessionWANConnectionStatus
oriPPPoESessionWANConnectionStatus.description: This object represents the state of the PPPoE WAN connection interface.

oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTable.name: oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTable
oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTable.description: This table is used to map client MAC address to PPPoE Session information for an ISP.

oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableEntry.name: oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableEntry
oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the PPPoE MAC to Session table.

oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableIndex.name: oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableIndex
oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index to the PPPoE Session Table.

oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableMACAddress.name: oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableMACAddress
oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableMACAddress.description: This object represents the client MAC address.

oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableISPName.name: oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableISPName
oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableISPName.description: This object represents the ISP name.

oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableStatus.name: oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableStatus
oriPPPoEMACtoSessionTableStatus.description: This object represents the PPPoE MAC to Session table entry status.

oriConfigResetToDefaults.name: oriConfigResetToDefaults
oriConfigResetToDefaults.description: This object represents the quickstart modes that the device can be configured in.

oriConfigFileTable.name: oriConfigFileTable
oriConfigFileTable.description: This table contains the current configuration files stored in the device. This table is used to manage the different configuration files.

oriConfigFileTableEntry.name: oriConfigFileTableEntry
oriConfigFileTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the configuration file table.

oriConfigFileTableIndex.name: oriConfigFileTableIndex
oriConfigFileTableIndex.description: This object represents the index to the configuration file table.

oriConfigFileName.name: oriConfigFileName
oriConfigFileName.description: This object represents the configuration file name.

oriConfigFileStatus.name: oriConfigFileStatus
oriConfigFileStatus.description: This object represents the status of the configuration file. The possible options are: - Enable: active configuration file - Disable: inactive configuration file - Delete: in order to delete the configuration file

oriConfigSaveFile.name: oriConfigSaveFile
oriConfigSaveFile.description: This object saves the configuration to the specified name.

oriConfigSaveKnownGood.name: oriConfigSaveKnownGood
oriConfigSaveKnownGood.description: This object is used to identify the last know good configuration file used. Setting a value of 1 to this objecgt saves the current configuration as the known good configuration.

oriDNSRedirectStatus.name: oriDNSRedirectStatus
oriDNSRedirectStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the DNS Redirect functionality.

oriDNSRedirectMaxResponseWaitTime.name: oriDNSRedirectMaxResponseWaitTime
oriDNSRedirectMaxResponseWaitTime.description: This object represents the maximum response wait time for DNS redirect. The units for this object is seconds.

oriDNSPrimaryDNSIPAddress.name: oriDNSPrimaryDNSIPAddress
oriDNSPrimaryDNSIPAddress.description: This object represents the Primary DNS IP Address.

oriDNSSecondaryDNSIPAddress.name: oriDNSSecondaryDNSIPAddress
oriDNSSecondaryDNSIPAddress.description: This object represents the Secondary DNS IP Address.

oriDNSClientStatus.name: oriDNSClientStatus
oriDNSClientStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the DNS Client feature.

oriDNSClientPrimaryServerIPAddress.name: oriDNSClientPrimaryServerIPAddress
oriDNSClientPrimaryServerIPAddress.description: This object represents the Primary Server DNS IP Address.

oriDNSClientSecondaryServerIPAddress.name: oriDNSClientSecondaryServerIPAddress
oriDNSClientSecondaryServerIPAddress.description: This object represents the Secondary Server DNS IP Address.

oriDNSClientDefaultDomainName.name: oriDNSClientDefaultDomainName
oriDNSClientDefaultDomainName.description: This object represents the default domain name for the DNS Client.

oriAOLNATALGStatus.name: oriAOLNATALGStatus
oriAOLNATALGStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the AOL NAT Application Level Gateway (ALG) support.

oriNATStatus.name: oriNATStatus
oriNATStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the NAT feature.

oriNATType.name: oriNATType
oriNATType.description: A Bit Mask documenting the NAT device's actual configuration according to natTypeMask above. Its value may be one and only one of the options below: - Basic-NAT (Bit 0) - NAPT (Bit 1) - Bi-directional-NAT (Bit 2) - Twice-NAT (Bit 3) - RSA-IP-Server (Bit 4) - RSAP-IP-Server (Bit 5) - Bit 0, if set, indicates that Basic-NAT is configured. - Bit 1, if set, indicates that NAPT is configured. - Bit 2, if set, indicates that Bi-directional-NAT is configured. - Bit 3, if set, indicates that Twice-NAT is configured. - Bit 4, if set, indicates that RSA-IP-Server is configured. - Bit 5, if set, indicates that RSAP-IP-Server is configured.

oriNATStaticBindStatus.name: oriNATStaticBindStatus
oriNATStaticBindStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable static bind entries on the NAT device.

oriNATPublicIPAddress.name: oriNATPublicIPAddress
oriNATPublicIPAddress.description: This object is used to provide information on the NAT public IP Address.

oriNATStaticIPBindTable.name: oriNATStaticIPBindTable
oriNATStaticIPBindTable.description: This table contains NAT IP bind specific information.

oriNATStaticIPBindTableEntry.name: oriNATStaticIPBindTableEntry
oriNATStaticIPBindTableEntry.description: This object is an entry in the NAT Static IP Bind Table.

oriNATStaticIPBindTableIndex.name: oriNATStaticIPBindTableIndex
oriNATStaticIPBindTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index for the NAT static IP bind table.

oriNATStaticIPBindLocalAddress.name: oriNATStaticIPBindLocalAddress
oriNATStaticIPBindLocalAddress.description: This object represents the local IP address for this NAT Static IP bind Table entry.

oriNATStaticIPBindRemoteAddress.name: oriNATStaticIPBindRemoteAddress
oriNATStaticIPBindRemoteAddress.description: This object represents the remote IP address for this NAT Static IP bind Table entry.

oriNATStaticIPBindTableEntryStatus.name: oriNATStaticIPBindTableEntryStatus
oriNATStaticIPBindTableEntryStatus.description: The object indicates the status of the NAT Static IP Bind Table entry.

oriNATStaticPortBindTable.name: oriNATStaticPortBindTable
oriNATStaticPortBindTable.description: This table is used to configure NAT Port bind specific information.

oriNATStaticPortBindTableEntry.name: oriNATStaticPortBindTableEntry
oriNATStaticPortBindTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the NAT Static Port Bind Table.

oriNATStaticPortBindTableIndex.name: oriNATStaticPortBindTableIndex
oriNATStaticPortBindTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index for the NAT static Port bind table.

oriNATStaticPortBindLocalAddress.name: oriNATStaticPortBindLocalAddress
oriNATStaticPortBindLocalAddress.description: This object represents the local IP address for this NAT Static Port bind Table entry.

oriNATStaticPortBindStartPortNumber.name: oriNATStaticPortBindStartPortNumber
oriNATStaticPortBindStartPortNumber.description: This object represents the start port number for this NAT Static Port bind Table entry.

oriNATStaticPortBindEndPortNumber.name: oriNATStaticPortBindEndPortNumber
oriNATStaticPortBindEndPortNumber.description: This object represents the end port number for this NAT Static Port bind Table entry.

oriNATStaticPortBindPortType.name: oriNATStaticPortBindPortType
oriNATStaticPortBindPortType.description: This object represents the port type for this NAT Static Port bind Table entry.

oriNATStaticPortBindTableEntryStatus.name: oriNATStaticPortBindTableEntryStatus
oriNATStaticPortBindTableEntryStatus.description: The object indicates the status of the NAT Static Port Bind Table entry.

oriSpectraLinkStatus.name: oriSpectraLinkStatus
oriSpectraLinkStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the SpectraLink VoIP feature.

oriSpectraLinkLegacyDeviceSupport.name: oriSpectraLinkLegacyDeviceSupport
oriSpectraLinkLegacyDeviceSupport.description: This object is used to enable/disable SpectraLink VoIP support for legacy SpectraLink devices/phones.

oriVLANStatus.name: oriVLANStatus
oriVLANStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the VLAN feature.

oriVLANMgmtIdentifier.name: oriVLANMgmtIdentifier
oriVLANMgmtIdentifier.description: This object represents the VLAN management Identifier (ID).

oriVLANIDTable.name: oriVLANIDTable
oriVLANIDTable.description: This table is used to configure the VLAN IDs for the device. This table has been deprecated.

oriVLANIDTableEntry.name: oriVLANIDTableEntry
oriVLANIDTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the respective table. In this case each table entry represents a VLAN ID. This object has been deprecated.

oriVLANIDTableIndex.name: oriVLANIDTableIndex
oriVLANIDTableIndex.description: This object represents the index to the VLAN ID Table. This object has been deprecated.

oriVLANIDTableIdentifier.name: oriVLANIDTableIdentifier
oriVLANIDTableIdentifier.description: This object represents the VLAN Identifier (ID). This object has been deprecated.

oriDMZHostTable.name: oriDMZHostTable
oriDMZHostTable.description: A table containing DMZ host IP information. Only if the system is in Gateway mode, and the NAT is enabled, and this table has valid 'enabled' entry, the DMZ takes effect.

oriDMZHostTableEntry.name: oriDMZHostTableEntry
oriDMZHostTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the DMZ host IP Table.

oriDMZHostTableIndex.name: oriDMZHostTableIndex
oriDMZHostTableIndex.description: This object is used as the index for the DMZ host IP Table.

oriDMZHostTableHostIP.name: oriDMZHostTableHostIP
oriDMZHostTableHostIP.description: This object represents the DMZ host IP address.

oriDMZHostTableComment.name: oriDMZHostTableComment
oriDMZHostTableComment.description: This objecgt is used for an optional comment associated to the DMZ host IP Table entry.

oriDMZHostTableEntryStatus.name: oriDMZHostTableEntryStatus
oriDMZHostTableEntryStatus.description: The object indicates the status of the DMZ host IP Table entry.

oriOEMName.name: oriOEMName
oriOEMName.description: This object is used to specify the OEM name.

oriOEMHomeUrl.name: oriOEMHomeUrl
oriOEMHomeUrl.description: This object is used to specify the OEM home URL.

oriOEMProductName.name: oriOEMProductName
oriOEMProductName.description: This object represents the product name. It is the same name as shown in all management Web pages.

oriOEMProductModel.name: oriOEMProductModel
oriOEMProductModel.description: This object represents the product model.

oriOEMLogoImageFile.name: oriOEMLogoImageFile
oriOEMLogoImageFile.description: This object represents the name of logo image file.

oriOEMNoNavLogoImageFile.name: oriOEMNoNavLogoImageFile
oriOEMNoNavLogoImageFile.description: This object represents the name of no nav. logo image file.

oriStationStatTable.name: oriStationStatTable
oriStationStatTable.description: This table contains wireless stations statistics.

oriStationStatTableEntry.name: oriStationStatTableEntry
oriStationStatTableEntry.description: This object represents an entry in the respective table. In this case each table entry represents a wireless station.

oriStationStatTableIndex.name: oriStationStatTableIndex
oriStationStatTableIndex.description: This object represents the index of the stations statistics table. This table is limited to 500 entries.

oriStationStatTableMACAddress.name: oriStationStatTableMACAddress
oriStationStatTableMACAddress.description: This object represents the MAC address of the station for which the statistics are gathered.

oriStationStatTableIPAddress.name: oriStationStatTableIPAddress
oriStationStatTableIPAddress.description: This object represents the IP address of the stations for which the statistics are gathered. If the IP address is not known, 0.0.0.0 will be returned.

oriStationStatTableInterface.name: oriStationStatTableInterface
oriStationStatTableInterface.description: This object represents the number of the interface on which the station is last seen.

oriStationStatTableName.name: oriStationStatTableName
oriStationStatTableName.description: This object represents the name of the station. If the name is not known, an empty string will be returned.

oriStationStatTableType.name: oriStationStatTableType
oriStationStatTableType.description: This object represents the type of station.

oriStationStatTableMACProtocol.name: oriStationStatTableMACProtocol
oriStationStatTableMACProtocol.description: This object represents the MAC protocol for this station.

oriStationStatTableAdminStatus.name: oriStationStatTableAdminStatus
oriStationStatTableAdminStatus.description: This object represents the administrative state for the station. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

oriStationStatTableOperStatus.name: oriStationStatTableOperStatus
oriStationStatTableOperStatus.description: This object represents the current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

oriStationStatTableLastChange.name: oriStationStatTableLastChange
oriStationStatTableLastChange.description: This object represents the value of sysUpTime at the time the station entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

oriStationStatTableLastState.name: oriStationStatTableLastState
oriStationStatTableLastState.description: This object represents the last state of this station.

oriStationStatTableInOctets.name: oriStationStatTableInOctets
oriStationStatTableInOctets.description: The total number of octets received from the station, including framing characters.

oriStationStatTableInUcastPkts.name: oriStationStatTableInUcastPkts
oriStationStatTableInUcastPkts.description: This object represents the number of unicast packets from the station that are further processed by either by the bridge/router or by the internal host.

oriStationStatTableInNUcastPkts.name: oriStationStatTableInNUcastPkts
oriStationStatTableInNUcastPkts.description: This object represents the number of non-unicast packets (i.e. broadcast or multicast) from the station that are further processed by either by the bridge/router or by the internal host.

oriStationStatTableInDiscards.name: oriStationStatTableInDiscards
oriStationStatTableInDiscards.description: This object represents the number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to the internal bridge/router or the internal host. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to lack of buffer space.

oriStationStatTableOutOctets.name: oriStationStatTableOutOctets
oriStationStatTableOutOctets.description: This object represents the total number of octets send to the station, including framing characters.

oriStationStatTableOutUcastPkts.name: oriStationStatTableOutUcastPkts
oriStationStatTableOutUcastPkts.description: This object represents the number of packets that the internal bridge/router or the internal host requested be transmitted to the station, including those that were discarded or not sent.

oriStationStatTableOutNUcastPkts.name: oriStationStatTableOutNUcastPkts
oriStationStatTableOutNUcastPkts.description: This object represents the number of packets that the internal bridge/router or the internal host requested be transmitted to a non-unicast (i.e. broadcast or multicast) address that includes the station. This counter includes those packets that were discarded or not sent.

oriStationStatTableOutDiscards.name: oriStationStatTableOutDiscards
oriStationStatTableOutDiscards.description: This object represents the number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to the internal bridge/router or the internal host. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to lack of buffer space.

oriStationStatTableInSignal.name: oriStationStatTableInSignal
oriStationStatTableInSignal.description: This object represents the current signal level calculated over the inbound packets from this station. This variable indicates the running average of the local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriStationStatTableInNoise.name: oriStationStatTableInNoise
oriStationStatTableInNoise.description: This object represents the current noise level calculated over the inbound packets from this station. This variable indicates the running average of the local noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriStationStatTableRemoteSignal.name: oriStationStatTableRemoteSignal
oriStationStatTableRemoteSignal.description: This object represents the current remote signal level calculated over the inbound packets from this station on the remote station. This variable indicates the running average of the remote signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriStationStatTableRemoteNoise.name: oriStationStatTableRemoteNoise
oriStationStatTableRemoteNoise.description: This object represents the current remote noise level calculated over the inbound packets from this station on the remote station. This variable indicates the running average of the remote noise level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriStationStatTableLastInPktTime.name: oriStationStatTableLastInPktTime
oriStationStatTableLastInPktTime.description: This object represents the value of sysUpTime at the time the last packet from the remote station was received.

oriStationStatStatus.name: oriStationStatStatus
oriStationStatStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the monitoring of the wireless station statistics.

oriStationStatNumberOfClients.name: oriStationStatNumberOfClients
oriStationStatNumberOfClients.description: This object represents the number of active wireless clients associated to the access point.

oriSNTPStatus.name: oriSNTPStatus
oriSNTPStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable the SNTP functionality.

oriSNTPPrimaryServerNameOrIPAddress.name: oriSNTPPrimaryServerNameOrIPAddress
oriSNTPPrimaryServerNameOrIPAddress.description: This object represents the primary SNTP server IP address or host name.

oriSNTPSecondaryServerNameOrIPAddress.name: oriSNTPSecondaryServerNameOrIPAddress
oriSNTPSecondaryServerNameOrIPAddress.description: This object represents the secondary SNTP server IP address or host name.

oriSNTPTimeZone.name: oriSNTPTimeZone
oriSNTPTimeZone.description: This parameter is used for the device to know how to adjust GMT for local time.

oriSNTPDateAndTime.name: oriSNTPDateAndTime
oriSNTPDateAndTime.description: This object represents the Date and Time. The format of this object is the same as the DateAndTime textual convention.

oriSNTPDayLightSavingTime.name: oriSNTPDayLightSavingTime
oriSNTPDayLightSavingTime.description: This parameter indicates the number of hours to adjust for Daylight Saving Time.

oriSNTPYear.name: oriSNTPYear
oriSNTPYear.description: This object represents the year. This object can be used to manually configure the year in case the Date and Time is not retrieved from an SNTP server.

oriSNTPMonth.name: oriSNTPMonth
oriSNTPMonth.description: This object represents the month. This object can be used to manually configure the month in case the Date and Time is not retrieved from an SNTP server.

oriSNTPDay.name: oriSNTPDay
oriSNTPDay.description: This object represents the day of the month. This object can be used to manually configure the year in case the Date and Time is not retrieved from an SNTP server.

oriSNTPHour.name: oriSNTPHour
oriSNTPHour.description: This object represents the hour of day. This object can be used to manually configure the hour in case the Date and Time is not retrieved from an SNTP server.

oriSNTPMinutes.name: oriSNTPMinutes
oriSNTPMinutes.description: This object represents the minutes. This object can be used to manually configure the minutes in case the Date and Time is not retrieved from an SNTP server.

oriSNTPSeconds.name: oriSNTPSeconds
oriSNTPSeconds.description: This object represents the number of seconds. This object can be used to manually configure the seconds in case the Date and Time is not retrieved from an SNTP server.

oriConfigurationTraps.name: oriConfigurationTraps
oriConfigurationTraps.description: This is the configuration related trap/notification group.

oriTrapDNSIPNotConfigured.name: oriTrapDNSIPNotConfigured
oriTrapDNSIPNotConfigured.description: This traps is generated when the DNS IP Address has not been configured. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapRADIUSAuthenticationNotConfigured.name: oriTrapRADIUSAuthenticationNotConfigured
oriTrapRADIUSAuthenticationNotConfigured.description: This trap is generated when the RADIUS authentication information has not been configured. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapRADIUSAccountingNotConfigured.name: oriTrapRADIUSAccountingNotConfigured
oriTrapRADIUSAccountingNotConfigured.description: This trap is generated when the RADIUS accounting information has not been configured. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapDuplicateIPAddressEncountered.name: oriTrapDuplicateIPAddressEncountered
oriTrapDuplicateIPAddressEncountered.description: This trap is generated when the device has encountered another network device with he same IP Address. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapDHCPRelayServerTableNotConfigured.name: oriTrapDHCPRelayServerTableNotConfigured
oriTrapDHCPRelayServerTableNotConfigured.description: This trap is generated when the DHCP relay agent server table is empty or not configured. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapWORPIfNetworkSecretNotConfigured.name: oriTrapWORPIfNetworkSecretNotConfigured
oriTrapWORPIfNetworkSecretNotConfigured.description: This trap is generated when the system network authentication shared secret is not configured. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapVLANIDInvalidConfiguration.name: oriTrapVLANIDInvalidConfiguration
oriTrapVLANIDInvalidConfiguration.description: This trap is generated when a VLAN ID configuration is invalid. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapAutoConfigFailure.name: oriTrapAutoConfigFailure
oriTrapAutoConfigFailure.description: This trap is generated when the auto configuration failed. Trap Severity Level: Minor.

oriTrapBatchExecFailure.name: oriTrapBatchExecFailure
oriTrapBatchExecFailure.description: This trap is generated when the CLI Batch execution fails for the following reasons. - Illegal Command is parsed in the CLI Batch File. - Execution error is encountered while executing CLI Batch file. - Bigger File Size than 100 Kbytes Trap Severity Level: Minor.

oriTrapBatchFileExecStart.name: oriTrapBatchFileExecStart
oriTrapBatchFileExecStart.description: This trap is generated when the CLI Batch execution begins after file is uploaded. Trap Severity Level: Minor.

oriTrapBatchFileExecEnd.name: oriTrapBatchFileExecEnd
oriTrapBatchFileExecEnd.description: This trap is generated when the execution of CLI Batch File Ends. Trap Severity Level: Minor.

oriSecurityTraps.name: oriSecurityTraps
oriSecurityTraps.description: This is the security related trap/notification group.

oriTrapInvalidEncryptionKey.name: oriTrapInvalidEncryptionKey
oriTrapInvalidEncryptionKey.description: This trap is generated when an invalid encryption key has been detected. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapAuthenticationFailure.name: oriTrapAuthenticationFailure
oriTrapAuthenticationFailure.description: This trap is generated when a client authentication failure has occurred. The authentication failures can range from: - MAC Access Control Table - RADIUS MAC Authentication - 802.1x Authentication specifying the EAP-Type - WORP Mutual Authentication - SSID Authorization Failure specifying the SSID - VLAN ID Authorization Failure specifying the VLAN ID Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapUnauthorizedManagerDetected.name: oriTrapUnauthorizedManagerDetected
oriTrapUnauthorizedManagerDetected.description: This trap is generated when an unauthorized manager has attempted to view and/or modify parameters. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapRADScanComplete.name: oriTrapRADScanComplete
oriTrapRADScanComplete.description: This trap is generated when an a RAD scan is successfully completed. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapRADScanResults.name: oriTrapRADScanResults
oriTrapRADScanResults.description: This trap is generated in order to provide information on the RAD Scan results. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapRogueScanStationDetected.name: oriTrapRogueScanStationDetected
oriTrapRogueScanStationDetected.description: This trap is generated when a rogue station is detected. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapRogueScanCycleComplete.name: oriTrapRogueScanCycleComplete
oriTrapRogueScanCycleComplete.description: This trap is generated when an a rogue scan is successfully completed. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriWirelessIfTraps.name: oriWirelessIfTraps
oriWirelessIfTraps.description: This is the wireless interface or wireless card related trap/notification group.

oriTrapWLCNotPresent.name: oriTrapWLCNotPresent
oriTrapWLCNotPresent.description: This trap is generated when a wireless interface/card is not present in the device. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapWLCFailure.name: oriTrapWLCFailure
oriTrapWLCFailure.description: This trap is generated when a general failure has occured with the wireless interface/card. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapWLCRemoval.name: oriTrapWLCRemoval
oriTrapWLCRemoval.description: This trap is generated when the wireless interface/card has been removed from the device. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapWLCIncompatibleFirmware.name: oriTrapWLCIncompatibleFirmware
oriTrapWLCIncompatibleFirmware.description: This trap is generated when the firmware of the wireless interface/card is incompatible. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapWLCVoltageDiscrepancy.name: oriTrapWLCVoltageDiscrepancy
oriTrapWLCVoltageDiscrepancy.description: This trap is generated when a non 5 volt card or 3.3 volt wireless interface/card is inserted in the device. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapWLCIncompatibleVendor.name: oriTrapWLCIncompatibleVendor
oriTrapWLCIncompatibleVendor.description: This trap is generated when an incompatible wireless vendor card is inserted or present in the device. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapWLCFirmwareDownloadFailure.name: oriTrapWLCFirmwareDownloadFailure
oriTrapWLCFirmwareDownloadFailure.description: This trap is generated when a failure occurs during the firmware download process of the wireless interface/card. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapWLCFirmwareFailure.name: oriTrapWLCFirmwareFailure
oriTrapWLCFirmwareFailure.description: This trap is generated when a failure occurs in the wireless interface/card firmware. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapWLCRadarInterferenceDetected.name: oriTrapWLCRadarInterferenceDetected
oriTrapWLCRadarInterferenceDetected.description: This trap is generated when radar interference is detected on the channel being used by the wireless interface. The generic trap varible provides information on the channel where interference was detected. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriOperationalTraps.name: oriOperationalTraps
oriOperationalTraps.description: This is the operational related trap group group.

oriTrapUnrecoverableSoftwareErrorDetecte.name: oriTrapUnrecoverableSoftwareErrorDetected
oriTrapUnrecoverableSoftwareErrorDetecte.description: This trap is generated when an unrecoverable software error has been detected. This trap can signify that a problem/error has occurred with one or more software modules. This error would cause the software watch dog timer to expire which would then cause the device to reboot. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapRADIUSServerNotResponding.name: oriTrapRADIUSServerNotResponding
oriTrapRADIUSServerNotResponding.description: This trap is generated when no response is received from the RADIUS server(s) for authentication requests sent from the RADIUS client in the device. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapModuleNotInitialized.name: oriTrapModuleNotInitialized
oriTrapModuleNotInitialized.description: This trap is generated when a certain software or hardware module has not been initialized or failed to be initialized. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapDeviceRebooting.name: oriTrapDeviceRebooting
oriTrapDeviceRebooting.description: This trap is generated when the device has received a request to be rebooted. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapTaskSuspended.name: oriTrapTaskSuspended
oriTrapTaskSuspended.description: This trap is generated when a task in the device has suspended. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapBootPFailed.name: oriTrapBootPFailed
oriTrapBootPFailed.description: This trap is generated when a response to the BootP request is not received, hence the access point device is not dynamically assigned an IP Address. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapDHCPFailed.name: oriTrapDHCPFailed
oriTrapDHCPFailed.description: This trap is generated when a response to the DHCP client request is not received, hence the access point device is not dynamically assigned an IP Address. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapDNSClientLookupFailure.name: oriTrapDNSClientLookupFailure
oriTrapDNSClientLookupFailure.description: This trap is generated when the DNS client attempts to resolve a specified hostname (DNS lookup) and a failure occurs. This could be the result of the DNS server being unreachable or returning an error for the hostname lookup. This trap specified the hostname that was being resolved. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapSNTPFailure.name: oriTrapSNTPFailure
oriTrapSNTPFailure.description: This trap is generated when SNTP service is enabled and no response is received from the configured SNTP servers. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapMaximumNumberOfSubscribersReached.name: oriTrapMaximumNumberOfSubscribersReached
oriTrapMaximumNumberOfSubscribersReached.description: This trap is generated when maximum number of suscribers has been reached. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapSSLInitializationFailure.name: oriTrapSSLInitializationFailure
oriTrapSSLInitializationFailure.description: This trap is generated when the SSL initialization fails. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapWirelessServiceShutdown.name: oriTrapWirelessServiceShutdown
oriTrapWirelessServiceShutdown.description: This trap is generated when the Wireless Service Shutdown object is configured to down; in other words the wireless interface has shutdown services for wireless clients. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapWirelessServiceResumed.name: oriTrapWirelessServiceResumed
oriTrapWirelessServiceResumed.description: This trap is generated when the Wireless Service Shutdown object is configured to up; in other words the wireless interface has resumed service and is ready for wireless client connections. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapSSHInitializationStatus.name: oriTrapSSHInitializationStatus
oriTrapSSHInitializationStatus.description: This trap is generated to provide information on SSH initialization. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapVLANIDUserAssignment.name: oriTrapVLANIDUserAssignment
oriTrapVLANIDUserAssignment.description: This trap is generated when a user gets assigned a VLAN ID from the RADIUS server. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapDHCPLeaseRenewal.name: oriTrapDHCPLeaseRenewal
oriTrapDHCPLeaseRenewal.description: This trap is generated when the access point does a DHCP renewal request and receives new information from the DHCP server. The variables/objects bound to this trap will provide information on the DHCP server IP address that replied to the DHCP client request, and the IP address, subnet mask, and gateway IP address returned from the DHCP server. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapTemperatureAlert.name: oriTrapTemperatureAlert
oriTrapTemperatureAlert.description: This trap is generated when the temperature crosses the limit of -30 to 60 degrees celsius. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriFlashTraps.name: oriFlashTraps
oriFlashTraps.description: This is the flash memory related trap group.

oriTrapFlashMemoryEmpty.name: oriTrapFlashMemoryEmpty
oriTrapFlashMemoryEmpty.description: This trap is generated when there is no data present in flash memory - either on the flash card or the onboard flash memory. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapFlashMemoryCorrupted.name: oriTrapFlashMemoryCorrupted
oriTrapFlashMemoryCorrupted.description: This trap is generated when the data content of flash memory is corrupted. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapFlashMemoryRestoringLastKnownGood.name: oriTrapFlashMemoryRestoringLastKnownGoodConfiguration
oriTrapFlashMemoryRestoringLastKnownGood.description: This trap is generated when the current/original configuration data file is found to be corrupted, therefore the device will load the last known good configuration file. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTFTPTraps.name: oriTFTPTraps
oriTFTPTraps.description: This is the TFTP related trap group.

oriTrapTFTPFailedOperation.name: oriTrapTFTPFailedOperation
oriTrapTFTPFailedOperation.description: This trap is generated when a failure has occurred with the TFTP operation. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapTFTPOperationInitiated.name: oriTrapTFTPOperationInitiated
oriTrapTFTPOperationInitiated.description: This trap is generated when a TFTP operation has been initiated. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapTFTPOperationCompleted.name: oriTrapTFTPOperationCompleted
oriTrapTFTPOperationCompleted.description: This trap is generated when a TFTP operation has been completed. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriMiscTraps.name: oriMiscTraps
oriMiscTraps.description: This is the miscellaneous trap group.

oriImageTraps.name: oriImageTraps
oriImageTraps.description: This is the image related trap group.

oriTrapZeroSizeImage.name: oriTrapZeroSizeImage
oriTrapZeroSizeImage.description: This trap is generated when a zero size image is loaded on the device. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapInvalidImage.name: oriTrapInvalidImage
oriTrapInvalidImage.description: This trap is generated when an invalid image is loaded on the device. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapImageTooLarge.name: oriTrapImageTooLarge
oriTrapImageTooLarge.description: This trap is generated when the image loaded on the device exceeds the size limitation of flash. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapIncompatibleImage.name: oriTrapIncompatibleImage
oriTrapIncompatibleImage.description: This trap is generated when an incompatible image is loaded on the device. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapInvalidImageDigitalSignature.name: oriTrapInvalidImageDigitalSignature
oriTrapInvalidImageDigitalSignature.description: This trap is generated when an image with an invalid Digital Signature is loaded in the device. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriWORPTraps.name: oriWORPTraps
oriWORPTraps.description: This is the WORP related trap group.

oriWORPStationRegister.name: oriWORPStationRegister
oriWORPStationRegister.description: This trap is generated when a WORP satellite has registered on and interface of a base; a satellite will not generate this trap, but use oriWORPLinkUp instead. For the station indicated, the oriStationStatTableOperStatus will be up. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriWORPStationDeRegister.name: oriWORPStationDeRegister
oriWORPStationDeRegister.description: This trap is generated when a WORP satellite has been deleted from an interface of a base; a satellite will not generate this trap, but use oriWORPLinkDown instead. For the station indicated, the oriStationStatTableOperStatus will be down. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriSysFeatureTraps.name: oriSysFeatureTraps
oriSysFeatureTraps.description: This is the System Feature based License related trap group.

oriTrapIncompatibleLicenseFile.name: oriTrapIncompatibleLicenseFile
oriTrapIncompatibleLicenseFile.description: This trap is generated when a license file in the device's flash memory is not compatible with the current bootloader. Trap Severity Level: Major.

oriTrapFeatureNotSupported.name: oriTrapFeatureNotSupported
oriTrapFeatureNotSupported.description: This trap is generated when a feature present in the license codes is not supported by the current embedded software image. A newer embedded software image could support the feature or there are more license that needed. Trap Severity Level: Informational.

oriTrapZeroLicenseFiles.name: oriTrapZeroLicenseFiles
oriTrapZeroLicenseFiles.description: This trap is generated when a single license file is not present in flash. This causes the device to operate in default mode with very limited features enabled. Trap Severity Level: Critical.

oriTrapInvalidLicenseFile.name: oriTrapInvalidLicenseFile
oriTrapInvalidLicenseFile.description: This trap is generated when a license file in the device's flash memory has an invalid signature and will be ignored. Trap Severity Level: Minor.

oriTrapUselessLicense.name: oriTrapUselessLicense
oriTrapUselessLicense.description: This trap is generated when a license code file does not contain any valid feature code. The probably reason for this is that after verification, not any of the features was meant for this units MAC address. Trap Severity Level: Informational.
